Dr. Faisal Mir is a distinguished graduate of Howard University College of Dentistry. He completed his residency training at the College of Physicians & Surgeons of Columbia University in New York City, New York. Dr. Mir is trained as a general dentist focusing on cosmetic, and restorative dentistry. He has extensive training in endodontic therapy (root canal treatment), and periodontal surgery (gum treatment). He is also a Certified Invisalign Preferred Provider (clear braces). Dr. Mir values the importance of high quality patient care and satisfaction. He has extensive knowledge and experience using state of the art technology and techniques to ensure his patient’s dental visit is a pleasant one. Dr. Mir is a member of the Academy of General Dentistry, American Dental Association, DC Dental Society, and Virginia Dental Association. He continues to attend educational seminars to provide his patients with the latest treatment options using evidenced-based and cutting-edge technological advances and methods. For fun, he enjoys hiking, traveling, spending time with his family and getting to know different cultures around the world.
education: Howard University College of Dentistry
experience: Completed residency training at the College of Physicians & Surgeons of Columbia University in New York City, New York. Extensive training in endodontic therapy and periodontal surgery. Certified Invisalign Preferred Provider.

full_bio: Dr. Tefesehet Mesfin, the founder of 202 Dental Care, believes in providing a truly relaxing dental services focused on excellence and patient comfort. It’s her aim to make you feel so relaxed it feels like sipping coffee with an old friend. Dr. Mesfin has been practicing dentistry in Washington, D.C. for the last six years serving patients living and working in the Washington Metropolitan region. A two-time Ivy league graduate, Dr. Mesfin graduated from University of Pennsylvania in Biomedical Engineering. She then earned her Doctor of Dental Surgery from the Columbia University in New York City. Philippines Dental mission trip She continued her studies by completing a post-doctoral residency in general dentistry at Bronx-Lebanon Hospital in NYC. While working at the Hospital she focused her time on root canal treatments, oral surgery, bridges, and crowns. Dr. Mesfin is a strong believer in continuing education; she continually fortifies and develops her dentistry skills by completing extensive continuing education programs each year. She wants to stay on top of the latest leading-edge dental developments to offer patients complete, individualized dental care including cosmetic, restorative and surgical services. Dr. Mesfin is proud to be a member of the American Dental Association. When not providing top-quality dental care to her valued patients or working pro bono to make a difference, Dr. Mesfin's multicultural interests extend to travel, photography, spinning, and spending time with family and friends. Dr. Mesfin's vision of a dentistry based on kindness and comfort is underlined by her pro bono work locally and internationally in Ethiopia, Cambodia, Guatemala, and the Philippines. Her goal is to provide the less fortunate around the world with the dental care that they deserve - because everyone smiles in the same language! As a member of the Washington DC community, Dr. Mesfin believes her fellow citizens deserve the very best in dental care. She is pleased to offer leading-edge treatments in a comforting environment where the patient really does come first.
education: University of Pennsylvania in Biomedical Engineering, Columbia University in New York City (Doctor of Dental Surgery), post-doctoral residency in general dentistry at Bronx-Lebanon Hospital in NYC
experience: Practicing dentistry in Washington, D.C. for the last six years

full_bio: Dr. Thaddeus Harvey Jr. was born in Macon, Georgia and raised in Roberta, GA . A product of the local public school system, Dr. Harvey was faced with limited resources. With help from dedicated faculty and staff, he made the best of his situation and thrived in primary school . In his spare time, he managed to letter in sports and participate in many volunteer events around his community. While in high school, he was given the opportunity to participate in the Pipeline Prehealth program at Fort Valley State University. This pre-med program would prove to be the building blocks of his career in healthcare. Upon graduation from High school with honors, Dr. Harvey matriculated to Fort Valley State University. While in college, Dr. Harvey remained active in the Pipeline Prehealth program. He also shadowed several healthcare providers and found an affinity to the field of dentistry. Dr. Harvey began Dental School at Howard University in the Fall of 2003 and graduated with honors in 2007. Upon graduation, he attended a general practice residency at Jackson Memorial Hospital in Miami, Florida. Today he practices dentistry in Atlanta, GA and finds most enjoyment in dental implantology. When away from work, he enjoys spending time with his lovely wife Candace and children, Zoe (5) and Carter (3).
education: Fort Valley State University; Howard University
experience: General practice residency at Jackson Memorial Hospital in Miami, Florida; practice dentistry in Atlanta, GA

full_bio: Dr. Candace Harvey was raised in the small, rural town of St. Matthews, South Carolina. She graduated from South Carolina State University, in Orangeburg, South Carolina, with a Bachelors of Science degree in Biology. Shortly afterwards, Dr. Harvey was accepted into Howard University College of Dentistry, in Washington, DC, where she obtained her Doctorate of Dental Surgery degree in May 2007. She then completed a one-year general practice residency at Saint Francis Hospital and Medical Center in Hartford, Connecticut. Dr. Harvey moved to the Atlanta metro area in 2009. After working with both adults and children, Dr. Harvey realized that her true passion was working with children. Although she is a General Dentist, Dr. Harvey has decided to devote her primary focus towards Pediatric Dentistry. Dr. Harvey is married and has two beautiful children. She enjoys traveling, reading and partaking in any outdoor sport or activity, but most important, she enjoys spending quality time with her husband, Thaddeus and their beautiful children, Zoe and Carter.
education: South Carolina State University; Howard University College of Dentistry
experience: One-year general practice residency at Saint Francis Hospital and Medical Center; focus on Pediatric Dentistry in Atlanta, GA

full_bio: Dr. Young's experience, training, and new technology will give you and your loved ones a brighter, healthier smile. We now offer complete dental implant and orthodontic treatment! As a family and implant dentist, Dr. Michael J. Young provides exceptional, compassionate care. With an office in Lafayette, Dr. Young performs a full range of dental services, from routine preventive cleanings to advanced restorative and cosmetic procedures. In every case, our team places great importance on patient comfort and convenience. That is why we proudly offer sedation options, convenient financing, and back-to-back appointments for family members. Dr. Young is also committed to ongoing education to bring you the latest treatment options. As a member of both the Academy of General Dentistry and the American Academy of Cosmetic Dentistry, he has undertaken rigorous training in contemporary procedures, such as dental implant placement and same-day crowns.
education: Dr. Young began his collegiate career at Louisiana State University at Eunice, where he studied basic science and nursing. He then moved on to Louisiana State University at Baton Rouge to pursue a biochemistry degree with the intent of applying to dental school. Dr. Young began his dental education at Louisiana State University (LSU) School of Dentistry in 1999 and graduated in 2003.
experience: He worked as an associate dentist and completed many hours of continuing education, including training in dental implants and cosmetic dentistry. After two years as an associate dentist, Dr. Young opened his own dental practice in 2005. Dr. Young completed dental implant training at Misch Resnik Implant Institute in California, in 2016-17. He has also completed the Progressive Orthodonitic Seminars Program, a part of the McGann Postgraduate School of Dentistry.

full_bio: Dr. Chong was born and raised in Toronto, Canada, where he studied at the University of Toronto obtaining his degree in Industrial Engineering and Applied Mathematics. Thereafter, he went on to complete his dental education at New York University where he graduated amongst the top of his class and was inducted into the Omicron Kappa Upsilon National Dental Honor Society. It is needless to say but his passion to educate has given him the opportunity to present case studies at conferences, lead study clubs, and train at world class dental institutions. Dr. Chong completed his orthodontic residency at the University of Illinois in Chicago while excelling at the top of his class with accolades such as winner of a National Invisalign Award. During his tenure at UIC he also obtained a Masters degree for his research involving the development of a novel method for analysis of tooth movement in 3D. Dr. Chong is a caring and talented dentist who possesses the highest qualifications and is well skilled in all aspects of orthodontics. He is an adept practitioner committed to providing the best care available personalized for each family member.
education: University of Toronto, New York University, University of Illinois
experience: Completed orthodontic residency; presented case studies; led study clubs; trained at world class dental institutions.

full_bio: After graduating dental school, Dr AlRubaie finished a 2 year residency program in advanced education in general dentistry from Miami, Florida and practiced for 6 years as a general dentist in Illinois and Florida. Afterwards, Dr AlRubaie joined a 3 year dual degree residency program in Periodontology and Master of Science at Nova Southeastern University/College of Dental medicine in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. Dr AlRubaie is a board eligible periodontist and has a great passion for his field. Dr AlRubaie did his Master thesis about dental implants and he has published in peer reviewed journals. During his spare time, He enjoys practicing kickboxing and travels for scuba diving spots all over the world.
education: Nova Southeastern University/College of Dental medicine
experience: Practiced for 6 years as a general dentist; completed dual degree residency in Periodontology.

full_bio: Meet The Team Always Feel Welcomed by Our New Orleans Dental Team Our New Orleans dental team is dedicated to providing compassionate, professional care. You’ll be treated like an individual at 7 O’Clock Dental, LLC, not a number. We enjoy getting to know our patients and creating an atmosphere that’s relaxing and casual. We’ll take time to answer all your questions and assist you with everything from scheduling to payment. You’ll always feel welcome at our office! Darlene Office Manager Darlene has worked in dentistry for more than three decades! She joined our team in 2015. Darlene has experience and training in radiology and as a CPR instructor. She enjoys teaching patients about their oral health. She likes painting, drawing, gardening, and family time.

full_bio: Born and raised in Tampa, Dr. Abdoney, also know as Mark is a third-generation dentist , having followed his grandfather, father, and mother into the field. He is dedicated to providing specialty periodontal care with an emphasis on personal attention, compassion, and excellent results. Dr. Abdoney is a graduate of the University of Florida , where he received a Bachelor of Science in 1992 and his Doctorate of Dental Medicine in 1996. He completed his periodontal residency at Nova Southeastern University in 2000. That same year, he received the Award of Periodontal Excellence from the NSU Department of Periodontics. Since graduating, Dr. Abdoney has been actively involved in the field of dentistry. He has served as president of the Florida Association of Periodontists and the Hillsborough County Dental Research Clinic, and has been on the board of the Hillsborough County Periodontal Association, the Florida Association of Periodontists, and the Southern Academy of Periodontology. He is an active member of the prestigious American College of Dentistry , the International College of Dentistry , and the Spear Institute . Along with these organizations, Dr. Abdoney has maintained a close association with the University of Florida as a current Associate Clinical Professor and works frequently with their Department of Pathology regarding a majority of patient biopsies. He is also a member of the Rotary Club, consistent with his hope of improving the health and education of not only his own patients but the community at large. Outside of his practice, Dr. Abdoney enjoys spending time with his four beautiful daughters and extended family. Growing up as a Boy Scout and in the outdoors in general, he is an avid outdoorsman. He loves to fish, dive, hunt, camp, hike, and surf. Earning a degree in zoology from the University of Florida, Dr. Abdoney takes particular interest in the many habitats and ecosystems the great state of Florida has to offer, as well as land management, animal husbandry, and agriculture. He also enjoys training in MMA and jiu-jitsu.
education: University of Florida , Bachelor of Science in 1992, Doctorate of Dental Medicine in 1996; Nova Southeastern University, periodontal residency in 2000
experience: Third-generation dentist; former president of the Florida Association of Periodontists and the Hillsborough County Dental Research Clinic; board member of the Hillsborough County Periodontal Association, the Florida Association of Periodontists, and the Southern Academy of Periodontology; Associate Clinical Professor at the University of Florida; active member of the American College of Dentistry, the International College of Dentistry, and the Spear Institute.

full_bio: Dr. Wiesner is the founder and CEO of A Brighter Smile Dental Care. He has more than 4,000 personal patients that come from 11 different states, some of which include Virginia, North Dakota, and Minnesota. His practice has received the Top Dentist Award from the prestigious Locals Love Us brand four years in a row. Dr. Wiesner donates many hours to local community events and has appeared on KTBS, KSLA, and Fox News. Among the charity events, he has hosted are Dentistry from the Heart, a day that offers free dental care to the community, and Free from Plaque for Veterans. The Free From Plaque Campaign, which offers free cleanings to veterans on Veteran’s Day, is a personal cause of Dr. Wiesner’s since he himself is a veteran of the United States Armed Forces: He has been stationed in Little Rock, Arkansas, and even England. He graduated from Louisiana State University of Shreveport with a degree in biochemistry and furthered his education at Louisiana State University’s School of Dentistry where he received his Doctorate of Dental Surgery. Post-graduation, Dr. Wiesner continues to enhance his dental portfolio by taking extra courses in dental implantology and IV sedation (a method that allows patients to receive extensive dental work while being in a complete state of relaxation or asleep .) Dr. Wiesner maintains an active membership with the American Dental Implant Association and the American Academy of Facial Esthetics . Collectively, he and his team have more than 75 years of experience in the dental field.
education: Graduated from Louisiana State University of Shreveport with a degree in biochemistry and Louisiana State University’s School of Dentistry where he received his Doctorate of Dental Surgery.
experience: Collectively, he and his team have more than 75 years of experience in the dental field.

full_bio: Dr. Thuy, General Family Dentist, is the co-founder and co-CEO of A Brighter Smile Dental Care. A Brighter Smile Dental Care has seen more than 11,000 patients since Dr. Thuy helped establish it in 2007. The practice has been featured in the Shreveport Times , and patients have come from as far as California, Utah, and Illinois to have work performed by Dr. Thuy. Her role in the practice’s orthodontic care won her Premier Provider for Invisalign® status in 2016. Dr. Thuy is an active contributor to local charities. Some of the charity campaigns she has been an instrumental part of are: the Shreveport Holy Angels Run for individuals with intellectual and developmental disabilities, Pay it Forward, and St. Jude’s Fight Against Childhood Cancer. She is an advocate for helping underprivileged children, and collects toys at A Brighter Smile Dental Care every holiday season for the local homeless shelter’s children. Dr. Thuy graduated from the University of New Orleans with her degree in biological sciences, as well as Louisiana State University’s School of Dentistry with her Doctorate of Dental Surgery. She is a member of the International Association for Orthodontics. Her desire to provide the highest quality of care for her patients is evident in her ongoing education and completion of additional education courses in sleep apnea and orthodontics. Dr. Thuy is certified by the American Academy of Facial Esthetics . Dr. Wiesner and Dr. Thuy are happily married with two beautiful children. Together, they work side by side to provide excellent dental care to their patients in the Shreveport-Bossier area.
education: Graduated from the University of New Orleans with her degree in biological sciences, as well as Louisiana State University’s School of Dentistry with her Doctorate of Dental Surgery.

full_bio: Dr. Milstead was born and raised in Shreveport. She completed her high school education at Caddo Magnet High School where she graduated with honors and proceeded to Louisiana State University Shreveport to work on her degree in biological sciences. With hard work, dedication, and a passion to pursue a career in dentist ry, she received early acceptance into dental school at Louisiana State University School of Dentistry in New Orleans where she received her Doctorate of Dental Surgery. Following graduation, she practiced in the New Orleans area for four years before returning to Shreveport to be closer to family and continue to care for patients in her hometown. Dr. Milstead has experience in treating patients of all ages, including children, and she is dedicated to providing them with high-quality dental care. She believes in giving them the most comfortable and gentle dental experience possible, and she feels that trust, comfort, communication, and compassion are the keys to a great doctor-patient relationship. Dr. Milstead has received several awards in prosthodontics and operative dentistry as well as the International College of Dentists Leadership Award. She has volunteered with Give Kids a Smile, participated in providing care on free treatment days in the Shreveport community, and traveled with a local church to provide free dental services in Mexico. She is currently a member of the American Dental Association , the Louisiana Dental Association , and the Northwest Louisiana Dental Association. When she’s not in the office, Dr. Milstead enjoys spending time with her eight horses, three dogs, and six cats. Dr. Milstead also loves traveling and attending LSU football games. Dr. Dr. Milstead is excited to be a part of A Brighter Smile Dental Care and looks forward to helping you take care of your smile!
education: Graduated with honors from Caddo Magnet High School and proceeded to Louisiana State University Shreveport to work on her degree in biological sciences. She received early acceptance into dental school at Louisiana State University School of Dentistry in New Orleans where she received her Doctorate of Dental Surgery.
experience: Dr. Milstead has experience in treating patients of all ages, including children.

full_bio: Dr. Hernandez was born in Havana, Cuba, and emigrated to Canada at age 12. Five years later she emigrated again to Miami, Florida where she finished High School. Given her international upbringing, she is also fluent in Spanish and French. Dr. Hernandez attended Florida International University and graduated with Honors with a Bachelor of Biological Sciences degree and a minor in Psychology. Her empathetic nature made her gravitate toward the medical field from an early age and decided to become a dentist where she could use her knowledge, skills, and training to help others improve their health and quality of life. Dr. Hernandez attended the University of Florida College of Dentistry where she obtained her Doctorate in Dental Medicine. Her artistic skills and passion for teaching other dental students led her to be a teacher assistant for Aesthetic Dentistry and Prosthodontics courses. She was also the president of the Hispanic Student Dental Association and coordinated an extracurricular clinic for underserved communities and migrant workers while in dental school. Upon graduation, Dr. Hernandez was awarded an American Prosthodontic Society Student Award of Merit and the American Association of Endodontics Student Award of Merit. Dr. Hernandez’s passion for uplifting and inspiring her patients to achieve a harmonious healthy smile is what drives her professional interests, which are centered on restorative sciences and include the fields of endodontics, prosthodontics, oral surgery, and implantology. Dr. Hernandez enjoys spending time with her Siberian Husky Piper, drawing, weight-lifting, and loves to read all kinds of books especially those recommended by her patients.
education: Graduated from Florida International University with Honors with a Bachelor of Biological Sciences degree and a minor in Psychology. Attended the University of Florida College of Dentistry where she obtained her Doctorate in Dental Medicine.

full_bio: Dr. Thomas grew up in Mesa, AZ where her family still currently resides running a Pediatric Pulmonary clinic and a horse ranch. After graduating from Desert Ridge High School in Mesa, AZ, Dr. Thomas attended Arizona State University to receive a bachelor’s degree in Biological Sciences with a minor in Dance. She furthered her education at the University of Colorado School of Dental Medicine and served in the United States Army for 4 years. After the military brought her family to Shreveport-Bossier, Dr. Thomas settled into practice with A Brighter Smile. Dr. Thomas has experience with patients who suffer from dental anxiety and strives to make all her patients as comfortable as possible in the dental chair. She puts great effort into building a personal connection with all her patients to ensure comfort, trust, and the best dental experience possible. Dr. Thomas specializes in CEREC dentistry, providing same-day permanent crowns to her community. She is also a member of the American Dental Association , Colorado Dental Association, and the American Academy of Facial Esthetics . Her continuing education includes further training in Endodontics, pediatrics, and cosmetic dentistry. In her spare time, Dr. Thomas loves to spend time with her family, be outdoors, and participate in events with her children. Dr. Thomas also loves training for physical fitness to include long-distance running, biking, weightlifting, and hiking. She is also an avid horseback rider, country music lover, and coffee drinker.
education: Received a bachelor’s degree in Biological Sciences with a minor in Dance from Arizona State University. Furthered her education at the University of Colorado School of Dental Medicine.

full_bio: Dr. Ricky Fox was born and raised in Shreveport, LA and practices in our Shreveport Suite 500 office. After graduating from Captain Shreve High School, Dr. Fox received his degree in medical sciences from Louisiana State University Shreveport. With a passion to follow in the footsteps of his father as a 4th generation medical/dental professional, Dr. Fox attended Louisiana State University School of Dentistry in New Orleans where he received his Doctorate of Dental Surgery. After graduation, Dr. Fox practiced in Chalmette, LA for two years before returning to Northwest Louisiana. He practiced at his own office, Bossier Dental Health Center, in Bossier City for seven years before moving back across the river to his hometown neighborhoods. In Shreveport, he continued his family's legacy and continued his late father's practice at Fox Family Dentistry, which was started the year Dr. Ricky Fox was born almost sixty years ago. Dr. Ricky is experienced in orthodontics, cosmetic dentistry, and sleep apnea treatment. He is a member of the Community of 100 at LSU School of Dentistry - giving back to his alma mater and supporting the education of future dentists. With thirty-two years of experience in general and family dentistry, Dr. Ricky is committed to providing excellent care while developing lasting patient-doctor relationships and lifelong friendships. In his free time, Dr. Ricky enjoys playing golf and tennis, hunting and fishing, and spending time with his lovely wife, family, and their 6 grandchildren. Dr. Ricky joined A Brighter Smile in late 2022 to enjoy the community of our team, work closely with other dentists, and be a part of a growing professional practice. He is excited to share his plethora of knowledge gained from his thirty-two years of experience. Dr. Ricky is grateful for the daily opportunity to provide care to patients today that his father once treated as children and having the role as the family dentist to 4th generation patients of his family's practice.
education: Received his degree in medical sciences from Louisiana State University Shreveport and attended Louisiana State University School of Dentistry in New Orleans where he received his Doctorate of Dental Surgery.
experience: With thirty-two years of experience in general and family dentistry.

full_bio: Dr. Christopher Marsalis was born and raised in Shreveport, Louisiana, only leaving the area to attend dental school. A graduate of Loyola College Prep, he went on to earn a Bachelor of Arts in Biology from Centenary College in 2016. He also completed additional coursework in the sciences at Louisiana State University in Shreveport before earning his Doctorate of Dental Surgery from LSU School of Dentistry in New Orleans. Before dental school, Dr. Marsalis took part in a rewarding volunteer opportunity through the Literacy Volunteers program at Centenary College, where he taught English as a second or third language to a small group of adult learners. During dental school, he served as a student ambassador, giving tours, participating in the admissions process, and hosting Q&A sessions for prospective students. In his free time, Dr. Marsalis enjoys spending time outdoors—especially on cool, sunny days—walking, running, biking, or traveling to the mountains for hiking trips. At home, he enjoys gardening and growing herbs, peppers, cucumbers, and microgreens. As the chef of the house, he loves experimenting with new recipes like coconut chicken curry with quinoa or homemade pizza in his portable pizza oven. Dr. Marsalis and his wife welcomed their first child in 2025 after nearly ten years of marriage, and he is grateful for the time he now spends caring for his growing family. Dr. Marsalis is proud to join the experienced team at A Brighter Smile Dental Care and is committed to providing exceptional care to every patient he serves.
education: A graduate of Loyola College Prep, he went on to earn a Bachelor of Arts in Biology from Centenary College in 2016 and earned his Doctorate of Dental Surgery from LSU School of Dentistry in New Orleans.

full_bio: Dr. Tony Liu was born and raised in Taiwan and has lived all around the world. He attended Northwestern University prior to completing dental school at the University of Illinois at Chicago College of Dentistry. He founded Acacia Family Dental 35 years ago and since then has provided quality care and a dental home for generations of patients. Outside of dentistry, Dr. Liu enjoys spending time with his wife and two daughters, especially traveling with them. He also enjoys playing tennis, riding his bike, and staying active.
education: Northwestern University; University of Illinois at Chicago College of Dentistry
experience: 35 years

full_bio: As an Orthodontic specialist, Dr. Lisa Mangiarelli is uniquely qualified to provide exceptional orthodontic care for children, adolescents, and adults. She has built her practice around attention to detail and loves creating beautiful smiles. She offers traditional orthodontic care, but especially enjoys treating complex cases involving smile design, jaw surgery, and orthodontic preparation for dental implants. She proudly works alongside her husband, Dr. David A Beltran, who is a Periodontist. Education A native of Western Pennsylvania, Dr. Mangiarelli completed her Bachelor of Science in Biology at Westminster College and her Doctorate of Dental Medicine from the University of Pittsburgh School of Dental Medicine, where she continued to maintain Dean’s List status. She then received a certificate in Orthodontics from Nova Southeastern University in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. Outside of the Office Dr. Mangiarelli and her husband have been practicing in Orlando for more than 15 years. She and her husband have two wonderful children. Outside the office, you can find her with her family at soccer tournaments, swim meets, or at the beach. Dr. Mangiarelli and her family are happy to be a part of such a great community and look forward to serving it for many years to come.
education: Bachelor of Science in Biology at Westminster College; Doctorate of Dental Medicine from the University of Pittsburgh School of Dental Medicine; certificate in Orthodontics from Nova Southeastern University in Fort Lauderdale, Florida.
experience: more than 15 years practicing in Orlando

full_bio: Founder/Owner of Access Dental Center Practicing general dentist for 25+ years Graduated from Case Western Reserve School of Dental Medicine
education: Graduated from Case Western Reserve School of Dental Medicine
experience: Practicing general dentist for 25+ years

full_bio: Graduated from Case Western Reserve School of Dental Medicine
education: Graduated from Case Western Reserve School of Dental Medicine

full_bio: Dr. Loftus was born in Sacramento, California. She completed her undergraduate degree at Syracuse University where she majored in Biomedical Engineering. She then went on to get her dental degree from the University of Southern California (USC) School of Dentistry. Since graduating from USC, Dr. Loftus has been an Associate Dentist at varying offices for the past 10 years prior to opening her own office. In her spare time, she loves to spend time with her three kids and her husband, hanging out at the beach, hiking, or going to any one of her kids sporting events. Fight On!
education: Syracuse University, University of Southern California (USC) School of Dentistry
experience: 10 years as Associate Dentist

full_bio: Hello, I am Dr. Rao. I have been practicing dentistry for more than 25 years, including 15 years right here in Northern California. I have a passion for dentistry and love what I do. I like to connect with people, understand why they have come to my office and take care of their dental needs. I strive to keep my skills current by constantly upgrading my knowledge with the latest technology through attending continuing education seminars and courses. I am a member of the American Dental Association® , the California Dental Association and the Northern California Dental Society . Beyond dentistry, I love animals, and I also do my best to help underprivileged communities. I love the Californian landscape and outdoors and often indulge in gardening, hiking and attending vintage automobile shows. I look forward to meeting you!
experience: 25 years

full_bio: Your smile plays an important part in almost everything you do. It is the first impression and a lasting one. That's why it's important for me to help you smile with confidence. I'll sit down with you and develop a plan that will help keep your teeth healthy and your smile the best it can be. If you have questions, it would be my pleasure to ensure that you understand all of your options and feel entirely comfortable with any and all treatment recommendations. Together, we will decide the best way to create the healthy, beautiful smile you've always wanted. Education: I graduated from Humboldt University, one of the most distinguished Universities in Germany. I received my doctor in dental surgery degree in 2000 and have been living and practicing in Orange and Riverside county since 2006. I am dedicated and passionate about consistently staying up-to-date in the latest technologies and techniques, therefore I attend over 200 hours a year of Continuing education in all facets of dentistry. Including Cosmetic, Sedation, Orthodontics ( braces and Clear Braces,Invisalign ),Pain management, Botox and Implant dentistry, . My education has formed the core of who I am today and has allowed me to provide quality dental care to my patients. With an emphasis on continued education, I am always learning in order to become the best dentist I can be.
education: I graduated from Humboldt University, one of the most distinguished Universities in Germany. I received my doctor in dental surgery degree in 2000.
experience: I have been living and practicing in Orange and Riverside county since 2006. I attend over 200 hours a year of Continuing education in all facets of dentistry.

full_bio: Dr. Swati Malik is the general dentist . Since her early high school aspirations, dentistry has been a means for Dr. Malik to raise spirits by restoring their smiles. Dr. Malik grew up in New Delhi , India obtained her initial degree in Bachelor of Dental Surgery ( BDS) and then graduated from Boston University School of Dental Medicine . Dr. Malik earned her Doctor of Dental Medicine (DMD) Degree from Boston University . Dr. Malik started practicing at dental practice that had been serving Weymouth and the surrounding communities for over 5 years. Through her clinic, Dr. Malik is further emboldened to provide quality and compassionate dental care to the families of Plymouth County. However, when she’s not working, Dr. Malik continues to raise the kids with her husband while also enjoying hiking, running, cooking, reading and the occasional trip to Disneyland.
education: Bachelor of Dental Surgery (BDS), Boston University School of Dental Medicine, Doctor of Dental Medicine (DMD)
experience: Started practicing at dental practice that had been serving Weymouth and the surrounding communities for over 5 years.

full_bio: Dr. Rahul Malik obtained his initial degree in Bachelor of Dental Surgery ( BDS) and then pursued a Master’s Degree in public health form University of Alabama at Birmingham . Upon completion of this advanced program, Dr. Malik was accepted at the prestigious Boston University Henry M. Goldman School of Dental Medicine . Educated on the latest technology and techniques the dental field has to offer, Dr. Malik earned his Doctor of Dental Medicine (DMD) Degree Dr. Rahul Malik is dedicated to quality dentistry and creating lasting relationships with our patients. His commitment to making each patient experience memorable is seen from the moment you enter our office door. His passion to incorporate technology in the practice has led to foundation of the state of art practice with top of the line sterilization techniques. Dr. Malik has spent numerous continuing education hours to hone his skills in various fields of dentistry ranging from but not limited to Implants, Invisalign, Root Canals, Cosmetic Dentistry and Oral Surgical procedures. He is a member of American Dental Association, Massachusetts Dental society Dr. Rahul Malik was able to earn Mastership status by International congress of Oral Implantologists ( ICOI ) and American Academy of Implant Prosthodontics ( AAIP ) by his efforts in education, research, and clinical experience – giving him the expert knowledge to perform dental implants at a recognized level. Dr. Malik joined the US Army just after dental school in 2012. He is currently serving as a O fficer in the United States Army Reserve . Dr. Malik prides himself in treating every single patient as if they were his immediate family. He holds a strict “open door” policy for patients and staff to ensure everyone understands their treatment plans, receives gentle care, and feels excited to book their next visit with us.
education: Bachelor of Dental Surgery (BDS), Master’s Degree in public health form University of Alabama at Birmingham, Boston University Henry M. Goldman School of Dental Medicine, Doctor of Dental Medicine (DMD)
experience: Dedicated to quality dentistry and creating lasting relationships with patients. Spent numerous continuing education hours to hone skills in various fields of dentistry. Joined the US Army just after dental school in 2012. Currently serving as an Officer in the United States Army Reserve.

full_bio: Dr. Zukerberg received her Doctor of Dental Medicine degree (DMD) from the University of Pennsylvania . Following earning her degree, she completed her general practice residency at Howard University Hospital in Washington, DC. She is a member of the American Dental Academy , the Washington Dental Society and American Academy of Cosmetic Dentistry . Dr. Zukerberg is dedicated to ongoing education and awareness of the latest advancements in dental medicine to improve services and patient care. She graduated from the Kois Center for Advanced Dentistry through Science in Seattle, Washington and is a member of Dental Study Club, where professionals meet on monthly basis to discuss various topics and developments of dentistry. Prior to opening her own practice, Dr. Zukerberg worked as a dental associate in Washington, DC. Dr. Zukerberg speaks English, Russian and Lithuanian.
education: Doctor of Dental Medicine degree (DMD) from the University of Pennsylvania. Howard University Hospital in Washington, DC.
experience: worked as a dental associate in Washington, DC.

full_bio: Gabriela Vatafu DDS, husband and wife, earned their DDS degree in 2005 at New York University, College of Dentistry. Driven by a strong commitment to quality dentistry, in 2008, they opened a dental practice in Newington. After gaining experience in managing a dental office, they wanted to extend their practice choosing Glastonbury as a new location. Enthusiastic about learning new techniques, they expand their professional knowledge through continuing education courses. Dr. Gabriela enjoys performing aesthetic procedures, like Veneers and Lumineers, and she is a certified Invisalign provider.
education: DDS degree in 2005 at New York University, College of Dentistry
experience: opened a dental practice in Newington in 2008, experience in managing a dental office, continuing education courses

full_bio: Lucian Vatafu DDS, husband and wife, earned their DDS degree in 2005 at New York University, College of Dentistry. Driven by a strong commitment to quality dentistry, in 2008, they opened a dental practice in Newington. After gaining experience in managing a dental office, they wanted to extend their practice choosing Glastonbury as a new location. Enthusiastic about learning new techniques, they expand their professional knowledge through continuing education courses. Dr. Lucian places Implants, and he is more pro-surgical procedures.
education: DDS degree in 2005 at New York University, College of Dentistry
experience: opened a dental practice in Newington in 2008, experience in managing a dental office, continuing education courses

full_bio: After attending Centennial High School in Bakersfield, Dr. Divelbiss (Dr. D) went on to graduate from Brigham Young University and from the University of Southern California School of Dentistry in 2008. He graduated at the top of his class, earning the Fixed Prosthodontics Award for advanced achievement in veneer, crown and bridge. He is a member of the American Dental Association, California Dental Association and Kern County Dental Society. In his spare time, he enjoys spending time with family and friends and traveling with his wife. Dr. D is bilingual and speaks both English and Spanish.
education: Brigham Young University, University of Southern California School of Dentistry

full_bio: Dr. Mortensen is a Bakersfield Native. He graduated from West High School and then pursued his Bachelor’s of Science degree in Biology from Cal State University, Bakersfield and his Doctor of Dental Medicine degree at University of Nevada, Las Vegas School of Dental Medicine. As planned, he returned to Bakersfield to establish his practice among family and friends. He is a member of the American Dental Association, California Dental Association and Kern County Dental Society. Dr. Mortensen is happily married with three children. His hobbies are playing and watching most sports, especially football, and he enjoys playing the drums. He is also bilingual in English and Spanish.
education: Cal State University, Bakersfield, University of Nevada, Las Vegas School of Dental Medicine

full_bio: After graduating from the Medical University of South Carolina in 1995, Dr. James Slaughter returned to Bakersfield to serve the dental needs in the community he loves. Prior to attending dental school, Dr. Slaughter met and married his sweetheart, Lisa, while both were studying at Brigham Young University in Provo, Utah. They have four children. Dr. Slaughter is a member of the American Dental Association, California Dental Association and Kern County Dental Society. In order to keep himself current with the ever-changing advances in dentistry, Dr. Slaughter participates in numerous educational courses, including a mini-residency in dental implant treatment and extensive studies in bioesthetic dentistry. Dr. Slaughter, an Eagle Scout himself, is an active leader in the Boy Scouts. He enjoys cycling, kayaking, small-boat sailing, camping and time with his family. Dr. Slaughter is bilingual in English and Spanish.
education: Medical University of South Carolina, Brigham Young University

full_bio: Dr. Hendricks is a Bakersfield native. She was born into a dental family comprised of dentists (grandfather and great-grandfather), a dental assistant (grandmother), dental hygienist (mother), and a dental lab technician (father). She decided to become a dentist while attending California State University Bakersfield. After graduating from Loma Linda School of Dentistry, she moved back to her hometown of Bakersfield, CA in 2006. She is a member of the American Dental Association, California Dental Association and Kern County Dental Society.
education: California State University Bakersfield, Loma Linda School of Dentistry

full_bio: Dr. Beemer has specialized in treating children since 1992. A graduate of the USC School of Dentistry in 1983, he completed a pediatric dentistry specialty residency at the Oregon Health Sciences University, School of Dentistry in Portland, Oregon in 1992. He served as President of the Kern County Dental Society in 2004 and maintains memberships in Kern County, California and American Dental Associations, as well as the American Academy of Pediatric Dentistry. Dr. Beemer and his wife have three children and enjoy cycling, traveling and quality time with their family.
education: USC School of Dentistry, Oregon Health Sciences University, School of Dentistry

full_bio: Sam Harouni, DDS is an experienced oral and maxillofacial surgeon, specializing in dental implants, extractions, TMJ surgery, and a variety of minimally invasive surgery techniques. His passion for helping patients achieve a bright, healthy smile is evident in his gentle, meticulous approach to dental surgery. Whether the aim is restoration, reconstruction, or rejuvenation, Dr. Harouni works with each patient to create an individualized treatment plan using the latest technologies in the most minimally invasive manner. After receiving his Bachelor of Science degree in Anthropology from UCLA in 2009, Dr. Harouni attended dental school at University of Southern California (USC), where he received his Doctorate of Dental Surgery (DDS) degree in 2013. Following his graduation from dental school, Dr. Harouni completed a year-long internship in Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery and Head & Neck Cancer at University of Florida, Jacksonville, followed by his Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery residency at Emory University School of Medicine, which is one of the leading research universities, and a top-ranking hospital in the U.S. Using the latest advancements in dental medicine, Dr. Harouni provides full mouth restorations, TMJ treatments, and bone grafting surgeries to enhance the quality of life in patients of all ages. He creates a custom treatment plan for each patient to ensure the best outcome. Dr. Harouni lives in Los Angeles, and in his personal time, he enjoys spending time with friends and family, hiking, biking, and skiing.
education: UCLA, University of Southern California (USC)

full_bio: Dr. Kmak is a practice owner at Associated Dentists of Northwest, Indiana. Dr. Kmak received his Bachelor of Arts from Indiana University, Bloomington. His Doctorate of Dental Surgery was earned from Indiana University School of Dentistry and he is also a member of the American Dental Association, the Indiana Dental Association and the Northwest Indiana Dental Society. Dr. Kmak has advanced training in cosmetic, restorative, endodontic and implant dentistry. Dr. Kmak is our only provider that makes himself available at our Merrillville location. Patient’s seek Dr. Kmak’s expertise because of his attention to detail, compassionate chair-side manner and drive to get every patient in pain help TODAY!
education: Bachelor of Arts from Indiana University, Bloomington; Doctorate of Dental Surgery from Indiana University School of Dentistry

full_bio: Dr. Williams is our veteran dental provider with over 40 years of experience 30 of which are here at Associated Dentists. Dr. Williams has practiced every facet of dentistry from military to private offices. Dr. Williams main focus is general dentistry and taking care of the patients over all dental health. Dr. Williams is adored amongst our patients and always goes above and beyond for them.
experience: over 40 years of experience, 30 years at Associated Dentists

full_bio: Dr. Woelfle completed his undergraduate studies at Duke University and continued at UCLA, where he received his DDS degree in 1988, and an advanced degree in hospital dentistry in 1989. Subsequently, he was chosen to train with an exclusive maxillofacial prosthodontic dental team in Santa Monica. In 1990, he relocated to San Francisco and practiced dentistry for fourteen years with a high-end large dental group at the Embarcadero Center. In 2004, with the inspiration of his mission statement, "Lead with excellence and serve with compassion" , he created and opened an ambitious and visionary office, Advanced Dentistry infusing it with cutting edge equipment to provide the highest quality procedures, and a uniquely designed friendly office that delivers effortless care along with the highest dental standards. Outside the office, Dr. Woelfle is an avid outdoorsman and tournament tennis player, who spends as much time as possible with his two sons. In the office, his ongoing focus is a commitment to mentoring and assembling the best team of doctors and staff to implement his mission, which should be evident in every step of a patient's experience, from arriving at the office, to follow up phone calls and care.
education: Duke University, UCLA
experience: Practiced dentistry for fourteen years with a high-end large dental group at the Embarcadero Center.

full_bio: As a native Las Vegan, I came to the San Francisco Bay Area to pursue my dream of becoming a dentist. In 1990, I graduated from The University of the Pacific School of Dentistry with High Honors. I continued in an Advanced Education in General Dentistry program for an additional two years. I have forever been an avid learner and continued to be so as I established my practice with the idea that people must be treated honestly and humanely. In addition to the traditional continuing education requirements needed to maintain my dental license, I also returned to school after a number of years in order to obtain my board certification in Naturopathic Medicine. I believe teeth are very important, but the old adage "only floss the ones you want to keep" falls way short of the mark. It's not just what the gums are doing in your mouth, but also what that bacteria is doing to the rest of your body. Whole body wellness is a big emphasis that I have and I work with other local practitioners to accomplish this approach. In addition to a busy practice, I juggle being a wife and mother of three and all around Type-A personality.
education: The University of the Pacific School of Dentistry

full_bio: We are currently gathering information for this biography. Please check back soon to read more about Dr. Tiller!

Graduating from University of the Pacific in 1994, Dr. Eslao's first year was spent working in her parent's dental office in Southern California. She then moved to the Central Valley to become associated in a group practice, where she stayed until 2000. The new millennium marked a time of inspiration and progression for Dr. Eslao when she decided to establish her roots in San Francisco. Most importantly, Dr. Eslao is known for her positive and caring attitude, as well as her superior standard in dentistry. The heart and soul of Dr. Eslao's practice are her patients, and she demonstrates her respect and regard for them through continued support, education, and safeguarding of their health (by herself and her staff). Her main focus is to empower patients to live balanced, harmonious, and healthy lives. It is this attitude that develops her aptitude in forging and building life-long relationships with her patients. She pursues continuing education with vigor, as her passion for dentistry draws her to scale new heights in patient care, cosmetic dentistry, and reconstructive dentistry. In order to maintain and diversify her base of experience and knowledge, she selects dental continuing education courses that will enable her to cultivate and develop her understanding of Dentistry. Among Dr. Eslao's crowning achievements are: The Pankey Institute (she is at level 4 of 6): a prestigious school that emphasizes treating patients as a whole, as opposed to one-dimensional diagnosis. Seattle Institute for Advanced Dental Education: focuses on patient occlusion and aesthetic dentistry. Pac Live: state-of-the-art techniques in aesthetic and cosmetic dentistry. Dr. Eslao is an active member of the San Francisco Dental Society, the Pankey Alumni Association, the UOP Alumni Association, the California Dental Association, the American Dental Association, the Academy of General Dentistry and the National Filipino Dental Association. She is in the top 1% of dentists in the country.
education: University of the Pacific

full_bio: Dr. Allan Pineda completed his dental degree at Centro Escolar University, College of Dentistry in Manila, Philippines in 1985. He then went to the United States to pursue further studies in dentistry. He was a Chicago-based dentist before moving in San Francisco, California to pursue International Dental Studies. He assumed a position as a dental teaching assistant in the Pediatric Department of the University of the Pacific in San Francisco, prior to completing his International Dental Studies at the same school, graduating in the top 10% of his International Dental Studies class in 2002. Before joining Advanced Dentistry, Dr. Pineda managed his own dental office in downtown San Francisco, Union Square for eight years. His practice provided pediatric, general family and cosmetic dentistry. He also finished a post-graduate course in cosmetic dentistry at the Northern California Institute of Cosmetic Dentistry in 2004. Currently, he holds a part-time faculty position at the University of the Pacific, School of Dentistry, in San Francisco. Teaching is also one of his passions in life; being with students and colleagues at the academy keeps him up-to-date on the current concept of dentistry. One of his principles in life is, "You never stop learning!" Outside the office, Dr. Pineda loves to sing show-tunes and Broadway musicals. He spend most of his time attending voice lessons, and he hopes to, maybe someday, perform on Broadway… a singing dentist!
education: Centro Escolar University, College of Dentistry
experience: Managed his own dental office in downtown San Francisco, Union Square for eight years.

full_name: Dr. Mike Maroon, DMD, FACE, FAGD
full_bio: With over 25 years of experience serving the Central Connecticut community, Dr. Mike Maroon is recognized as a leader in cosmetic and implant dentistry. Known for his artistic eye and attention to detail, Dr. Mike uses the latest dental technologies and materials to create beautiful, functional smiles. His passion for Functional Esthetic Dentistry has made him an authority in the field, with patients traveling from across the globe to achieve an original "Maroon" smile. Originally from Methuen, Massachusetts, Dr. Mike earned his Bachelor of Science from Marquette University and his Doctor of Dental Medicine from Tufts University. Throughout his career, Dr. Mike has remained at the forefront of dental advancements, earning Fellowships from the Academy of General Dentistry, the International Congress of Oral Implantologists, and more. His continuous pursuit of knowledge has included advanced training in Functional Orthodontics, Full-Mouth Restoration, and Implantology. Dr. Mike’s work extends beyond patient care—he has lectured internationally, published articles in major dental journals, and consulted with leading dental product manufacturers. Despite his many accolades, Dr. Mike is known for his warm and approachable demeanor. When not transforming smiles, he enjoys life in Central Connecticut with his wife and three daughters.
education: Bachelor of Science from Marquette University; Doctor of Dental Medicine from Tufts University
experience: Over 25 years of experience serving the Central Connecticut community

full_bio: Dr. Jadee Abbott brings a fresh and compassionate approach to cosmetic dentistry at Advanced Dental. Born and raised in Texas, Dr. Abbott graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Biology from Dallas Baptist University and earned her Doctorate of Dental Surgery from Texas A&M College of Dentistry. After practicing in both Alabama and California, she relocated to Connecticut, where she now serves patients with the same care and commitment that have defined her career. Dr. Abbott’s favorite part of her profession is building meaningful relationships with her patients. This connection allows her to provide truly personalized care, whether she’s performing routine procedures or designing life-changing clear aligner treatments. Her passion for continuing education ensures that she stays up to date with the latest technologies and techniques in modern dentistry. Outside the office, Dr. Abbott enjoys running, exploring Connecticut’s scenic hiking trails, and cheering on her beloved Auburn Tigers during college football season.
education: Bachelor of Science in Biology from Dallas Baptist University; Doctorate of Dental Surgery from Texas A&M College of Dentistry
experience: Practiced in Alabama and California before relocating to Connecticut

full_bio: Being a dentist is who I am and what I do. Each day I think of how I can improve the quality of my work, in order to provide patients with the advanced, quality dentistry they deserve. As a dentist, it is a pleasure to care for down-to-earth individuals and to share in their lives through the years. I appreciate that we can trade jokes, talk about mountain bike trails, or celebrate a new a member of their family, all while in a dental office. One of the most rewarding aspects of my career is having the ability to positively impact people’s lives. Whether relieving pain, offering practical education, addressing sleep disorders, or promoting overall health, with each interaction I can help people. I especially love restorative work and seeing people leave the office with new smiles, smiles they love and that will boost their confidence in life!
education: Utah State University, Bachelor of Science; Midwestern University, Doctorate of Dental Medicine
experience: Practiced in Phoenix until relocating to Grangeville, Idaho, in 2018. Dr. Brown has studied implant dentistry, as well as the use of dental lasers. Additionally, he has completed advanced training in sleep apnea.

full_bio: Mohamed Elnazer , DMD Dr. Mohamed Elnazer graduated in 2013 with high honors from Boston University-Henry M. Goldman School of Dental Medicine, where he was on the Dean's List. Eager to become the best dentist he could be, Dr. Elnazer immediately pursued his Advanced Education in General Dentistry (AEGD) Residency at the University of Texas Health Science Center San Antonio and successfully completed it as one of the most hard-working graduates of the program. After finishing his residency, he returned to Massachusetts where he worked in high-quality private practice settings until the summer of 2018. He then moved to Connecticut with his wife to enable her to pursue her residency at Yale Neurology. Dr. Elnazer started working at Advanced Dentistry of Connecticut in the summer of 2018 and purchased the practice in early 2021. Equipped with years of experience and mastery of dental skills, he provides his patients with high-quality, multidisciplinary, comprehensive dentistry in a family-oriented way. Patients and staff of Dr. Elnazer describe him as compassionate, knowledgeable, honest, and thorough. He works with an incredible staff who are sensitive to their patients' needs and have been serving their community for years with a smile and warm hearts. Dr. Elnazer believes that constantly evolving as a dentist through continuing education courses is essential to providing the best dental treatments available to his patients. He used to travel every week to attend aesthetics and full mouth rehabilitation courses at the prestigious Linhart Educational Center at NYU. He has also finished a residency in adult dental sleep medicine to treat patients with obstructive sleep apnea through oral appliances at Tufts Dental School and received Diplomate status from the American Board of Dental Sleep Medicine. The journey never stops. Outside of dentistry, Dr. Elnazer is an avid runner, completing the Baystate Marathon in Lowell, MA, and other Boston Area Half Marathons. He enjoys hiking, watching soccer, traveling, and spending time with his wife and kids.
education: Boston University-Henry M. Goldman School of Dental Medicine, University of Texas Health Science Center San Antonio, Tufts Dental School
experience: Worked in high-quality private practice settings until summer of 2018, started working at Advanced Dentistry of Connecticut in summer of 2018 and purchased practice in early 2021

Following dental school, Dr.Â BarkerÂ completed a rigorousÂ three year residency at Temple University School of DentistryÂ in Philadelphia, PA,Â where he earnedÂ his Specialty Certificate in Endodontics and aÂ Master of Science Degree inÂ Oral Biology in 2008.Â His intensiveÂ training at Temple emphasized theÂ mostÂ advanced technologies and up-to-date micro-endodontic techniques in order toÂ provideÂ exceptional quality ofÂ careÂ and highly predictiveÂ long term endodontic results.
