education: Bachelor of Science in Animal Physiology and Neuroscience from University of California San Diego; Dental training at the University of the Pacific School of Dentistry in San Francisco; Specialty Certificate in Endodontics and a Master of Science Degree in Oral Biology from Temple University School of Dentistry.
experience: Completed a rigorous three year residency at Temple University School of Dentistry in Philadelphia, involved in both the clinical and academic teaching of endodontics as an instructor and lecturer at Temple University, active in organized dentistry.

full_bio: Dr. Gal attended the University of Southern California where she graduated with honors from the dental hygiene program in 2003 and from the dental school in 2006. She was always a competitive student, excited about dentistry and has practiced in private practice since the day she graduated. Since then, she has focused on giving patients the most superb dental care, with experience and skill in all aspects of the dental field including implants, cosmetics, root canals and extractions. She continues to spend much time in sharpening her knowledge and giving the most advanced dental treatment that exists in todays’ market. She includes herself in many continuing education courses, and is a member of The American Dental Association (ADA), the California Dental Association (CDA), and the San Fernando Valley Association. She is kind, friendly, and is very gentle in her treatment of patients. She takes her time to explain procedures and makes her patients feel comfortable sitting in the dental chair.
education: University of Southern California, graduated with honors from the dental hygiene program in 2003 and from the dental school in 2006.
experience: Since graduation in 2006, focused on giving superb dental care, practiced in private practice, includes many continuing education courses.

full_bio: Dr. Tamir graduated the New York University School of Dentistry at the top of his class. He is focused on implantology and dental surgery as well as cosmetic dentistry. He attends many continuing education courses to keep the most advanced knowledge in implantology. Being that most of today’s patients are anxious about receiving dental care, he specializes in conscious oral sedation where patients don’t feel the treatment being rendered at all. He has over 10 years experience and is an expert in the overall aspects of dentistry. He is a member of The American Dental Association (ADA), the California Dental Association (CDA), the San Fernando Valley Association, and implantology seminars. He continuously receives the “Best Dentist of the Year” awards.
education: New York University School of Dentistry, graduated at the top of his class.
experience: Over 10 years experience, focused on implantology and dental surgery, specializes in conscious oral sedation.

full_bio: My name is Prakash Advani, and I have been a dentist for over 25 years. I have always had a passion for the field of dentistry and knew from a young age that I wanted to pursue a career in this field. I am excited to continue to grow and evolve as a dentist and I look forward to helping my patients achieve and maintain optimal oral health for many years to come. Education I completed my Bachelor of Dental Surgery (B.D.S.) at Nair Hospital Dental College. During my time in dental school, I gained a wealth of knowledge and experience through hands-on training and clinical rotations. I was particularly interested in aesthetic dentistry, and I took advantage of every opportunity to learn more about this field. Experience After graduating from dental school, I began my career as a dental associate at a busy health center in downtown San Jose, where I honed my skills and gained valuable experience treating patients of all ages. I am passionate about providing high-quality, personalized care to each of my patients and I always strive to stay up-to-date on the latest techniques and technologies in dentistry. I am now a proud owner of my own dental practice, Advani Dental Group, where I provide a wide range of dental services, from routine checkups and cleanings to more complex procedures such as root canal treatments, bone grafting, and sinus augmentations. Professional Associations I am committed to providing the highest standard of care to my patients and I am dedicated to building lasting relationships with them. In addition to my work as a dentist, I stay current on the latest developments in the field of dentistry and am actively involved in the community. I am involved in the following professional organizations: The American Dental Association The California Dental Association The Santa Clara County Dental Society
education: I completed my Bachelor of Dental Surgery (B.D.S.) at Nair Hospital Dental College.
experience: After graduating from dental school, I began my career as a dental associate at a busy health center in downtown San Jose, where I honed my skills and gained valuable experience treating patients of all ages. I am now a proud owner of my own dental practice, Advani Dental Group, where I provide a wide range of dental services, from routine checkups and cleanings to more complex procedures such as root canal treatments, bone grafting, and sinus augmentations.

full_bio: Natalie Mercho, DDS, obtained dual bachelor’s degrees in psychology and French from Indiana University in Bloomington and then traveled to the east coast to attend the University of Maryland School of Dentistry in Baltimore. She continued her studies after dental school in an effort to expand her skills and allow her to provide a broader range of care to her patients, completing two general practice residencies. At the Brooklyn Hospital Center in Brooklyn, NY, she became proficient in general dentistry skills such as periodontal (gum) treatment, pediatric care, and oral surgery. Later, at the Veterans Affairs Hospital in Baltimore, Maryland, she expanded her knowledge and skills with a greater concentration in cosmetic dentistry, endodontic (root canal) therapy, and implantology. Dr. Mercho is able to provide her patients with the healthy, beautiful smiles they deserve, and her dedication to patient satisfaction is second to none. Her patients can always be confident they are receiving the utmost dental care.

David Taler , DDS, FAGD, DABOI/ID, attended Franklin and Marshall College in Pennsylvania before receiving his dental degree from the University of Maryland School of Dentistry. He participated in the Advanced Education in General Dentistry Clerkship, where he developed advanced knowledge and expertise in implantology , oral surgery, endodontics, and cosmetic dentistry . He also joined the Baltimore Veterans Affairs residency program, where his leadership and dentistry skills earned him the Chief Resident position. Dedicated to lifelong education, he has achieved Fellowship in the American Academy of Implant Dentistry and the Academy of General Dentistry, Mastership in the International Congress of Oral Implantologists, and board-certified diplomate status with the American Board of Oral Implantology, the highest level of achievement in implant dentistry. As a decorated lacrosse player, he became a member of the Delphic Society, an organization recognizing individuals who achieve the highest levels of performance in academia, athletics, and community service.

Rachana Waghela, DDS, obtained her bachelor’s and dental degrees at the University of Missouri Kansas City, where she also completed her General Practice Residency. Her goal is to provide fearless and quality dentistry to her patients. She is passionate about helping her patients improve and maintain their oral health to lead a more confident life. She is also an artist by nature and by skill, and practicing dentistry helps her create beautiful smiles. Dr. Waghela is a member of the American Dental Association, Indiana Dental Association, Indianapolis District Dental Society, and Spear Study Club. She has a significant investment in continuing education with an emphasis on dental implant surgery. Away from the office, she is happily married and enjoys cooking, trying new restaurants, traveling and learning about different cultures, personal fitness, and painting. We thank you for your trust with all of your dental needs and look forward to providing you with excellent service and care!

Dr. Tyson A. Davis grew up in Mesa, Arizona and attended Mesa High School. He then attended Arizona State University and after one semester at ASU, he spent two years on a church mission in Valencia, Venezuela; where he learned to speak fluent Spanish. Upon returning from Venezuela, he continued his education at Brigham Young University where he studied Physiology and Developmental Biology. Dr Tyson Davis studied dentistry at the University of Pacific School Arthur A. Dugoni of Dentistry in beautiful San Francisco and graduated with his Doctor of Dental Surgery. He also received the TKO Honor Society Award for academic excellence. During his studies, Dr Tyson Davis learned all the new technologies and has implemented them into his practice. Dr. Davis has found dentistry to be very rewarding and is excited to grow his practice and have many new extended family members. While attending BYU, he met is wife Courtney and married before the start of dental school. During their time in dental school, they had their first son, Colter, and he is an absolute joy. They have since been blessed with tho beautiful daughters, Adalyn and Maya. Dr. Davis enjoys spending time with his family, playing all sports, especially golf, wake-boarding, riding quads and motorcycles, and simply being outdoors.
education: Arizona State University; Brigham Young University; University of Pacific School Arthur A. Dugoni of Dentistry
experience: Learned new technologies and implemented them into his practice. Found dentistry to be rewarding.

full_bio: Wallis grew up in southern Utah where he enjoyed the small town way of life. He rode his four wheeler to school and fished from local ponds. He enjoyed playing sports and spending late afternoons water-skiing with his friends. After attending the local college for a semester, he served a two year church mission in Pennsylvania. Upon returning form his mission, he continued his education at Dixie College where he met and married his wife, Suzanne. Upon graduating from Dixie College, the couple moved to Santa Ana, California where Ryan obtained a degree in Mortuary Science from Cypress College. Ryan began working at Metcalf Mortuary in St. George, Utah as a licensed funeral director. He enjoyed serving the families and eventually became a manager of one of the facilities. After 13 years and with a growing family, Ryan decided to further his education and applied to dental school. He was accepted into the Arizona School of Dental and Oral Health at A.T. Still University in Mesa, Arizona. With five children, the couple moved to Gilbert, AZ to start a new adventure. Their family fell in love with Arizona and decided to plant their roots here. Whether you see Dr. Wallis or Dr. Davis, you can expect the same great care that you are accustomed to receiving at Agave Dentistry.
education: Dixie College; Cypress College; Arizona School of Dental and Oral Health at A.T. Still University
experience: Licensed funeral director; manager at Metcalf Mortuary; further education to apply to dental school.

full_bio: Dr. Amy Nordquist is an Ahwatukee native who is excited to be providing dental care in her hometown! Providing patients with comprehensive and high quality care is of upmost importance to her as your dentist. You can feel confident knowing that you are in great hands with Dr. Nordquist.

Dr. Ailan Tran is a graduate of Loma Linda University of Southern California. She has been a dentist for more than 25 years, and has been through several post graduate courses in different fields of dentistry since receiving her DDS degree. Her emphasis on patients' comfort, as well as keeping up-to-date with the latest advancements in dentistry, enables her to provide her patients with the best quality of care in the field. Dr. Ailan Tran has a wide range of experience in different areas of dentistry, from preventive and restorative dentistry, surgical and endodontic treatments, to cosmetic treatments to enhance patients' smile. "I am proud to provide my patients with the best in dental technology, treatment options and patient comfort. I invite you to come to our beautiful dental office in San Jose. It is my pleasure to be your trusted provider of oral health care for years to come" Certificates : Mini Implants Advanced Training in Laser for Hard and Soft tissue Implant Prosthodontics CEREC ( Digital All Ceramic Fillings and Crowns in one day) Memberships : American Dental Association California Dental Association Santa Clara County Dental Society American Academy of Cosmetic Dentistry American Academy of Implant Dentistry Office hours are: Monday - Closed Tuesday - 9am -6pm Wednesday: 9am - 6pm Thursday - 9am - 6pm Friday, 9am - 6pm Saturday - 9am - 6pm Our Location and Contact Info. AILAN DENTAL CARE 2042 Tully Road San Jose, CA 95122 Tel: (408) 528-7878 Email: admin@ailandental.com Dental Website by Solution21 - Legal Notices - Sitemap
education: Loma Linda University of Southern California
experience: more than 25 years

full_bio: Meet our Director of Young Breath and Wellness, Terence Young, D.D.S., B.S., Respiratory Therapy Dr. Young graduated from University of the Pacific, Arthur A. Dugoni School of Dentistry, in San Francisco, California. After graduating from dental school in 1988, he moved back home to open his private dental practice in his hometown of Honolulu, Hawaii in 1990. Dr. Young’s Bachelor of Science degree is in Respiratory Therapy from Creighton University in Omaha, Nebraska. He provided Respiratory Therapy Services for Home Care residents on Kauai before attending dental school. He graduated high school from Punahou School, attended middle school at Kamehameha Schools and elementary at Hanahau’oli School. “My knowledge of respiratory physiology and general / airway dentistry helps me to better diagnose and treat our airway patients more effectively.” Dr. Young’s General and Airway Dental Practice actively treats dental and airway patients in ages from one to 102.
education: University of the Pacific, Arthur A. Dugoni School of Dentistry; Creighton University in Omaha, Nebraska
experience: Graduated from dental school in 1988; opened private dental practice in 1990; provided Respiratory Therapy Services

full_bio: Kimberly Tandarich has earned her Bachelor of Science Degree in Dental Hygiene from University of Hawaii at Manoa where she developed a strong foundation in dental science, preventive care, and patient education.She is a licensed dental hygienist, and is also certified in Orofacial Myofunctional Therapy. With a genuine interest in helping patients achieve and maintain optimal oral / airway well-being, Kimberly strives to make a positive impact on the well-being of those she serves. In her free time, Kimberly enjoys being active. She enjoys Pilates, hiking, stand up paddling, cooking and hanging with her French Bulldog.
education: Bachelor of Science Degree in Dental Hygiene from University of Hawaii at Manoa
experience: Licensed dental hygienist, certified in Orofacial Myofunctional Therapy

full_bio: Dr. Akhondi received her undergraduate degree in Biology with a minor in Chemistry from CA State University, Fullerton in 1995. She earned her Doctoral Degree in Dentistry from New York University in 1999 and then continued to practice dentistry for two years in Manhattan, NY. Dr. Akhondi moved to San Francisco and worked as an associate for ten years in Fremont and San Mateo offices before opening this practice in San Carlos, CA. She has been practicing dentistry for over 20 years. She has been living in Belmont with her husband and two daughters for the past 20 years. She loves the wilderness, hiking, biking, and camping with her family on the weekends.
education: CA State University, Fullerton in 1995; Doctoral Degree in Dentistry from New York University in 1999
experience: Practicing dentistry for over 20 years; worked as an associate for ten years in Fremont and San Mateo offices

full_bio: Born and raised in Foster City, California, Dr. Ota received her undergraduate degree in Neurobiology with a minor in Physiology and Behavior from UC Davis. Her dedication to academic excellence led her to pursue and achieve her Doctor of Dental Surgery degree with high academic honors from University of the Pacific - Arthur A Dugoni School of Dentistry. She is passionate about community dental health. Beyond her professional life, Dr. Ota enjoys traveling, hiking by the beach, and exploring the outdoors.
education: UC Davis; Doctor of Dental Surgery degree with high academic honors from University of the Pacific - Arthur A Dugoni School of Dentistry

full_bio: Dr. Richesin was raised in East Tennessee he completed his undergraduate studies at The University of Alabama and then earned his Doctor of Dental Medicine (DMD) from the University of Alabama at Birmingham. He joined Alabama Dental Associates in 1992. Practicing general dentistry, Dr. Richesin focuses on preventative, restorative and cosmetic procedures. Dr. Richesin is married with 2 sons. He enjoys cycling, auto racing and is active in his church.
education: The University of Alabama, Doctor of Dental Medicine (DMD) from the University of Alabama at Birmingham
experience: Joined Alabama Dental Associates in 1992, Practicing general dentistry

full_bio: Dr. Richerzhagen was born and raised in Birmingham. He attended The University of Alabama at Birmingham where he graduated with a bachelor’s degree in Natural Sciences and Mathematics. He earned his Doctor of Dental Medicine (DMD) at the University of Alabama at Birmingham School of Dentistry in 2000. He joined Alabama Dental Associates August of 2002. Dr. Richerzhagen is married and has two daughters. He enjoys football, going to the lake and is very active in his community.
education: The University of Alabama at Birmingham, Doctor of Dental Medicine (DMD) at the University of Alabama at Birmingham School of Dentistry
experience: Joined Alabama Dental Associates August of 2002

full_bio: Dr. Newdome graduated with a degree in Biomedical Chemical Engineering from Auburn University and graduated from The University of Alabama at Birmingham in 2007. He completed a one-year residency in General Dentistry at the Medical College of Georgia in Augusta. Dr. Newdome is married and is the proud father of two daughters and a son. He is an active deacon at Briarwood Presbyterian Church.
education: Biomedical Chemical Engineering from Auburn University, The University of Alabama at Birmingham
experience: Completed a one-year residency in General Dentistry at the Medical College of Georgia in Augusta

full_bio: Dr. Mark Alexander, a native of Twin Falls, graduated from the College of Idaho in 1988 Summa cum laude and Oregon Health Sciences University in 1992 cum laude. He has since practiced in Twin Falls with his uncle, Dr.Rich Alexander (who retired in June of 2013). Dr. Alexander has been very active in various dental organizations. He was the President of the South Central Idaho Dental Society. He has been a trustee with the Idaho State Dental Association (ISDA) . He's been a member of the Peer Review Committee of the ISDA since 1993, and serves as a component chair; he served as the state chair from 2007-2011. He served on the ISDA Strategic Planning Committee in 2007 and the Idaho Dental Foundation from 2007-2009 . He was fundraising chair of the ISDA Legislative Committee from 2011-2013. Mark currently serves on the Delta Dental of Idaho board. Dr. Alexander works with the CSI Dental Assisting/Hygiene program with in office training, and serves in the volunteer clinic. In his spare time, Dr. Alexander has served on the Twin Falls Library Foundation, the Episcopal Church Vestry, and has been a member of the Blue Lakes Rotary club for 20 years. Mark and his wife Larisa are busy with their 3 children. When time allows, Dr. Alexander loves to camp, fish, golf, and ski.
education: College of Idaho in 1988 Summa cum laude and Oregon Health Sciences University in 1992 cum laude
experience: He has since practiced in Twin Falls with his uncle, Dr.Rich Alexander (who retired in June of 2013). Dr. Alexander has been very active in various dental organizations. He was the President of the South Central Idaho Dental Society. He has been a trustee with the Idaho State Dental Association (ISDA) . He's been a member of the Peer Review Committee of the ISDA since 1993, and serves as a component chair; he served as the state chair from 2007-2011. He served on the ISDA Strategic Planning Committee in 2007 and the Idaho Dental Foundation from 2007-2009 . He was fundraising chair of the ISDA Legislative Committee from 2011-2013. Mark currently serves on the Delta Dental of Idaho board. Dr. Alexander works with the CSI Dental Assisting/Hygiene program with in office training, and serves in the volunteer clinic. In his spare time, Dr. Alexander has served on the Twin Falls Library Foundation, the Episcopal Church Vestry, and has been a member of the Blue Lakes Rotary club for 20 years.

full_bio: We use state-of-the-art technology to help build a sturdy foundation for your oral healthcare. At J. Alex Rang, DDS, we use our caring approach to give you the feeling of trust and comfort you look for when choosing a dentist. For those who need them, we offer dental implants, dentures, and partials, rebuilding great health from the ground up when dental damage has hurt your dental well-being and your smile confidence A Top Evansville, Indiana Dentist At Rang DDS in Evansville, Indiana we're more than just a top Evansville, Indiana dentist with quality dental care for the whole family. We're dedicated to every patient's oral health, well being and want to create a smile for you, from health to cosmetic dentistry, that you'll be proud of. Whether it's straightening your teeth or whitening them, crowns, bridges and more, the staff of Evansville, Indiana dentist, Alex Rang DDS will be with you every step of the way.

full_name: Francisco Eraso, DDS, MS, MS, MSD
full_bio: Dr. Francisco Eraso is an Oral and Maxillofacial Radiologist and an Orthodontist. He received his D.D.S. from Pontificia Universidad Javeriana, Bogota, Colombia, his advanced standing dental degree from Indiana University School of Dentistry, his M.S. in Oral Biology from the University of Louisville, his certificate and M.S. in Oral and Maxillofacial Radiology from The University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill and his Orthodontic Certificate and M.S.D. from Indiana University. Dr. Eraso is a former Associate Professor in the Department of Orthodontics at Indiana University, currently practices Orthodontics in Indianapolis and is one of the founding radiologists of Beamreaders Diagnostic Services. Dr. Eraso contributes as a reviewer for the American Journal of Orthodontics and Dentofacial Orthopedics, Angle Orthodontics, the Journal of Oral Surgery, Oral Medicine, Oral Pathology, Oral Radiology & Endodontics and the Journal of Dentomaxillofacial Radiology. Dr. Eraso has published several papers in the field and continues to lecture at various professional meetings and continued education courses nationally and internationally. Dr. Eraso is a member of numerous professional societies, including: American Dental Association, American Association of Orthodontists, American Academy of Oral and Maxillofacial Radiology and the International Association of Dentomaxillofacial Radiology. Dr. Eraso’s areas of interest include virtual dental solutions, digital orthodontics, imaging and 3D reconstruction, teleradiology and advanced imaging for Orthodontics, TMJ and Airways.
education: D.D.S. from Pontificia Universidad Javeriana, Bogota, Colombia, advanced standing dental degree from Indiana University School of Dentistry, M.S. in Oral Biology from the University of Louisville, certificate and M.S. in Oral and Maxillofacial Radiology from The University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, Orthodontic Certificate and M.S.D. from Indiana University.
experience: former Associate Professor in the Department of Orthodontics at Indiana University, currently practices Orthodontics in Indianapolis, founding radiologist of Beamreaders Diagnostic Services.

full_bio: Dr. Jimmy Chen was born in California and raised in Taiwan. He returned to Pennsylvania for high school and proceeded to graduate from Boston University with a B.S. degree in Biochemistry and Molecular biology and a minor in Japanese language and literature. Dr. Chen earned his D.M.D degree from Tufts University School of Dental Medicine. After graduation Dr. Chen received additional training as a dental resident at Hackensack Meridian Health Jersey Shore University Medical Center. During his residency, Dr. Chen honed his dental skills while treating the underserved population in the Jersey Shore area and taking care of dental emergency patients at the emergency room. Dr. Chen also attended monthly lectures given by renowned dentists and medical doctors. As dentistry is an ever-evolving field, Dr. Chen is focused on providing the most comprehensive and current care for his patients. Apart from staying updated with the latest dental research studies, Dr. Chen also takes continuing education courses year round. Dr. Chen is bilingual in English and Mandarin Chinese. Outside of dentistry, Dr. Chen enjoys watching various sports and documentaries along with cooking and traveling.
education: Boston University with a B.S. degree in Biochemistry and Molecular biology and a minor in Japanese language and literature; Tufts University School of Dental Medicine
experience: Dental resident at Hackensack Meridian Health Jersey Shore University Medical Center; treating underserved population; dental emergency patients

full_bio: Dr. Pei-Yun Kao was born in Taiwan and raised in California. She earned a B.S. degree in Human Physiology from the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA) and a D.M.D degree from Tufts University School of Dental Medicine. She worked as a dental assistant and a front office coordinator prior to becoming a dentist. Dr. Kao was inspired to pursue dentistry after shadowing and found her inner flow within the dental setting. She appreciates the beauty of dentistry in combining art, science, and oral and systemic health, while valuing each patient encounter to provide oral care and create smiles. While at UCLA, she received a full scholarship and was a part of the Academic Advancement Program. While at Tufts, she excelled in clinical training, worked as an extern at Boston Health Care Center for the Homeless Program serving the underserved population, and volunteered in the Tufts Sleep/TMD clinic. She was also actively involved in the American Student Dental Association as an elected representative/delegate for four years. Her proactive leadership made opportunities, resources, and events available to all student body, including dental advocacy, health and wellness, career planning and networking, and community oral healthcare outreach. She was awarded and honored as the ASDA National Delegate of the Year. As a first-generation college graduate and the first dentist in her family, Dr. Kao has always valued hard work, compassion, gratitude, and perseverance foremost in life. She embraces the same philosophy in her patient care. Dr. Kao values lifelong learning and actively takes continued education courses to stay current with forefront dental technology, materials, techniques to deliver the best comprehensive care possible to her patients. Dr. Kao is bilingual in English and Mandarin Chinese. Outside of dentistry, Dr. Kao enjoys cooking, reading, arts, and traveling.
education: B.S. degree in Human Physiology from the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA); D.M.D degree from Tufts University School of Dental Medicine
experience: Worked as a dental assistant and a front office coordinator; extern at Boston Health Care Center for the Homeless Program; volunteering in the Tufts Sleep/TMD clinic; involved in the American Student Dental Association

full_bio: Dr. Carla Alldredge is a native of Mt. Vernon, Indiana. She received her bachelor degree from the University of Southern Indiana in 2001 in Dental Hygiene Education. She later completed her Doctorate of Dental Medicine in 2005 from the University of Louisville School of Dentistry. After practicing as an associate dentist for two years, Dr. Alldredge established her own practice in 2007.
education: Bachelor degree from the University of Southern Indiana in 2001 in Dental Hygiene Education; Doctorate of Dental Medicine in 2005 from the University of Louisville School of Dentistry.
experience: Practiced as an associate dentist for two years before establishing her own practice in 2007.

full_bio: Dr. Allen grew up in Idaho, earning his Bachelor of Science in Biology from Idaho State University in 2002. He attended the Medical College of Virginia (Virginia Commonwealth University), graduating Magna Cum Laude with his Doctorate of Dental Surgery (DDS) in 2006. Following dental school, Dr. Allen was commissioned as a Captain in the United States Air Force and completed his Advanced Education in General Dentistry (AEGD) Residency at Bolling Air Force Base in Washington DC. This residency allowed him to expand his clinical knowledge and experience in all areas of dentistry. He offers a wide range of dental services including fillings, crowns and bridges, implant crowns, Invisalign clear braces, sedation and dental surgery, including wisdom teeth extractions. Dr. Allen loves Alaska because of the wonderful people and the many outdoor activities available here. He is an avid skier and is a member of the Anchorage Ski Club. He volunteers with Big Brothers and Big Sisters Alaska and donates dental services to the UAA Free Dental Day. He is also a Lieutenant Colonel in the United States Air Force Reserves on JBER and overseas the Dental Program at the 477th Fighter Group. Most of his free time revolves around his active and growing family. He and his wife, Virginie, love to travel and to explore (with a special affinity to her French homeland). They have four kids and love supporting them in their schooling, extracurricular activities, and sports. He is passionate about dentistry and loves making people smile. He believes a healthy mouth is an important component to a healthy and happy you!
education: Bachelor of Science in Biology from Idaho State University in 2002; Doctorate of Dental Surgery (DDS) in 2006 from Medical College of Virginia (Virginia Commonwealth University)
experience: Commissioned as a Captain in the United States Air Force; Completed Advanced Education in General Dentistry (AEGD) Residency at Bolling Air Force Base; Currently a Lieutenant Colonel in the United States Air Force Reserves overseeing the Dental Program at the 477th Fighter Group.

full_bio: Dr. Veranika Zakharyeva (“Dr. Z”) has the unique history of having grown up in Belarus and has lived in the United States since 2003. She earned her Bachelors of Philosophy degree from the University of West Florida in 2008. She attended the University of Oklahoma College of Dentistry and earned her Doctor of Dental Surgery (DDS) in 2013. Following graduation from dental school, Dr Zakharyeva commissioned as a Captain in the United States Air Force and completed Advanced Education in General Dentistry (AEGD) at Travis AFB in California. They were a true military family as her husband, Alexander, also served on active duty. During their active-duty Air Force careers, they were stationed all over the USA, including Florida, Alaska, and North Dakota, and overseas in Ramstein, Germany. Dr. Zakharyeva fell in love with Alaska when her family was stationed here for 3 years - this community truly felt like home. After her husband, Alexander, retired in 2023 from his 20-year Air Force career as Primary Care PA (Physician Assistant), they decided to start this new chapter of their lives by moving back to Anchorage. Dr. Z. and Alex are now young ‘empty nesters’ as their two sons are studying engineering at the Georgia Tech University and Maine Maritime Academy respectively. They are happy to be back and look forward to living the Great Alaskan Lifestyle with hiking, fishing, and camping. In her personal life, she enjoys traveling, reading, and making her home a welcoming place for family and friends. Professionally, Dr. Zakharyeva excels in general and family dentistry. In 2022, she was honored to be selected as the “Air Force Clinical Dentist of the Year (All USAF)”. This honor reflects highly on her clinical dental expertise and leadership abilities. Dr. Zakharyeva continues to serve her country as a Dental Officer in the 477th US Air Force Reserves on JBER, Alaska. She loves dentistry and taking care of her patients and is looking forward to meeting you!
education: Bachelors of Philosophy degree from the University of West Florida in 2008; Doctor of Dental Surgery (DDS) in 2013 from the University of Oklahoma College of Dentistry
experience: Commissioned as a Captain in the United States Air Force; Completed Advanced Education in General Dentistry (AEGD) at Travis AFB in California; Currently a Dental Officer in the 477th US Air Force Reserves on JBER, Alaska.

full_bio: My profession means being able to make an impact on kids’ lives, not just through their oral health now, but also by fostering positive feelings about visiting the dentist well into the future. Each child is so special, and I love seeing them grow up into healthy young adults with beautiful, healthy smiles! – Dr. Kristen Dr. Kristen Cummings was born and raised in a suburb of Chicago, Illinois. She attended the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign and graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in Biology. She then attended Southern Illinois University School of Dental Medicine where she received her Doctorate in Dental Medicine, cum laude. Because of her desire to specialize in pediatric dentistry, Dr. Kristen furthered her education by completing a two-year residency program at the Children’s Hospital in Denver, Colorado where she earned a Certificate of Specialization in Pediatric Dentistry. Dr. Kristen also chose to take part in a two-part examination, testing and validating her advanced training in pediatric dentistry. She completed these certifying exams, became a Diplomate of the American Board of Pediatric Dentistry, and is now a proud member of the ABPD College of Diplomates. In her spare time, Dr. Kristen enjoys traveling, staying active with her family, and playing tennis.
education: University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, Bachelor of Science degree in Biology; Southern Illinois University School of Dental Medicine, Doctorate in Dental Medicine, cum laude; two-year residency program at the Children’s Hospital in Denver, Colorado, Certificate of Specialization in Pediatric Dentistry.
experience: completed certifying exams, became a Diplomate of the American Board of Pediatric Dentistry

full_bio: Dr. Robling is originally from Petersburg, IN. She graduated from Pike Central High School and received her B.S. degree in Biology from Indiana University . After deciding at the age of 12 that being a dentist was her calling, she realized her dream by graduating in the top ten percent of her class from Indiana University School of Dentistry . Dr. Robling joined the team at All Smiles Dental in 2003. She has continued the "All Smiles" legacy of gentle, caring and affordable treatment. Dr. Robling is a member of the American Dental Association , the Indiana Dental Association , the Academy of General Dentistry , Ben Hur Dental Society, Omicron Kappa Upsilon Honor Dental Fraternity , and the American Academy of Facial Esthetics . She is a past president of the Ben Hur District Dental Society. Dr. Robling participates in numerous continuing education courses and is certified in sedation dentistry. She takes great pride in giving back to the community by sponsoring local teams and contributing to local charities. In her free time, Dr. Robling enjoys spending time with her children Rylen, Landry & Lyra.
education: Graduated from Pike Central High School, B.S. degree in Biology from Indiana University, graduated from Indiana University School of Dentistry.
experience: Joined the team at All Smiles Dental in 2003.

full_bio: Dr. Ronaldo Macam graduated in 1986, obtaining his Doctor of Dental Medicine degree from the University of the East. He is a Professional member of American Dental Association, Chicago Dental Association and Illinois Dental Association. With more than 20 years in experience, he practices dentistry at AllSmiles Family Dental Center in Niles, Illinois.
education: Doctor of Dental Medicine degree from the University of the East
experience: more than 20 years

full_bio: Providing dentistry for children requires a calling. As a profession, it requires having a strong clinical skill set, a keen understanding of medical conditions, knowledge and application of child psychology, and most importantly, compassion and patience. I have always enjoyed working with children and adolescents, and love being able to help them with their oral health needs. Each day, as I meet with new patients and their parents, I challenge myself to make a positive impact during their visit. Many parents come burdened with fear, from their own past experiences, wishing their child will not have to go through the same. I am reminded daily of the responsibility parents place in my hands, to treat their children with the utmost care and respect. I listen to my patients’ concerns and strive to provide a caring, safe environment in which to have their treatment. It is through each encounter, one patient at a time, that we are able to make a difference in the lives of those we are honored to serve. I provide lip and tongue tie treatment using a soft tissue laser. I have been trained and certified to use the dental laser since 2002. Click here to read more about this procedure and how it may assist your child. Education and Continuing Education Board Certified, American Board of Pediatric Dentistry Loma Linda University Doctorate of Dental Surgery Loma Linda University, Master of Science in Pediatric Dentistry Loma Linda University, Master of Public Health in Health Administration Loma Linda University, Master of Science in Physiology Johns Hopkins University , Graduate Studies University of Maryland at College Park , Bachelor of Science in Physiology and Neurobiology World Clinical Laser Institute Each year I attend lectures and simulations, and take online courses, to gain knowledge of the latest trends and techniques in treating pediatric dental patients. From 2003 to 2017 I have served as Assistant Professor of Pediatric Dentistry at Loma Linda University, where I delivered lectures and participated in research. I know that learning is a lifelong process. Currently, I serve as a Lecturer with the Department of Pediatric Dentistry at Loma Linda University and as a Guest Lecturer at San Diego State University . I am also an invited speaker for the Emergency Medicine Department Residents at University of California, Davis . As a board-certified pediatric dentist I take additional courses that other pediatric dentists do not take, further enhancing my knowledge and expertise in the field of pediatric dentistry. By participating in continuing education courses, I am developing my knowledge base, which allows me to learn new ways to help treat my patients. Professional Memberships American Board of Pediatric Dentistry, Diplomate American Academy of Pediatric Dentistry American Dental Association California Dental Association San Diego County Dental Society Personal Life I fell in love with San Diego when I was in high school. So shortly after completing my residency program I decided to move to San Diego to start career. My wife, Lisa, and I met while students at Loma Linda University; she is a speech therapist. When I’m not caring for my patients or teaching, I enjoy exploring San Diego; whether that’s running at Mission Bay, exploring the tidepools near Cabrillo, or wandering the museums at Balboa Park. I also enjoy playing tennis, reading nonfiction, and overseas mission trips. I am passionate about providing dental care for children in underserved communities. I have had the opportunity to provide dental care for pediatric patients in Mexico, Bolivia, Ecuador, Ethiopia, and Papua New Guinea. Being able to share my skills and help a child is incredibly rewarding. Locally, I serve on an appointed committee through the San Diego County Dental Society. I also serve as a volunteer dentist at Clinic with a Heart , which offers a free dental treatment program. Additionally, I volunteer my time with the San Diego Mission, a homeless ministry in downtown San Diego. I am an active member of the Escondido Seventh-day Adventist Church . I look forward to meeting you and your child.

full_bio: Orthodontist Improving Lives with Beautiful Smiles My patients are like a second family to me. Each is unique and brings his or her own personality to the office. I enjoy getting to know patients personally while helping them achieve a beautifully healthy smile — one they’ll love for a lifetime! Our smiles are how we greet the world. When people have crooked teeth, they often feel self-conscious and uncomfortable at school and work. Patients start orthodontics with low self-esteem and a reluctance to engage with their peers. As they see their teeth start to move into proper position, these people begin to feel better about themselves. They make eye contact and walk taller. Best of all, they start to talk happily and laugh with others, and to share their smile. By the time they finish, each is a new person: smiling with confident ease! I am passionate about the lasting difference orthodontic care makes. Although many think of braces as being all about smiles, the reality is that properly positioned teeth improve oral health and make it easier to keep your teeth and gums healthy and clean. Orthodontics also means better function and less strain on the jaw, which lessens the likelihood of TMJ-TMD in the future. My profession enables me to improve lives by helping people I care about to achieve beautiful smiles. I can’t imagine anything more rewarding! Education and Continuing Education Bachelor of Science in biochemistry – University of California, Berkeley Doctorate of Dental Surgery – Columbia University Certificate in orthodontics – Columbia University Each year, I complete many hours of continuing education here in Hawaii and abroad. Orthodontics is constantly evolving, and I want to use the best technologies and techniques available. These make the orthodontic experience as effective and comfortable as possible for my patients. I’ve been an Elite Preferred Provider for Invisalign® treatment (reserved for the top 1% of providers nationwide) since 2008 and am a Pacific Northwest Regional Leader. I am one of only a handful of women in the world to have earned this title. I have successfully treated more than 1,000 patients with Invisalign and can accomplish outstanding results! Professional Memberships Hawaii Society of Orthodontists Pacific Coast Society of Orthodontists American Association of Orthodontists American Dental Association Hawaii Dental Association California Dental Association Beyond the Office After growing up in Korea, I call Honolulu my home. My husband is Dr. Michon Morita and I’m Mom to two beautiful children. Being with my family is important to me, and I enjoy playing the piano.

Originally from Peru and with an international background, Dr. Evelyn Clemente graduated at the top of her class from Universidad Peruana Cayetano Heredia in Lima, Peru in 1997. She first had her Dental Hygientist license in Florida and later She pursued a two years International Dental Program graduating with a Cum Laude Honors at University of Buffalo, NY . During her academic career she has emphasized the importance of research and evidence based technology. She has been always up to date with the new technology and continuing education. ​ Dr. Clemente has decided to combine her experiences and create Amazing Smile to serve families with a profoundly educational and earth-friendly perspective. She offers a very unique approach to oral care for the entire family. Amazing Smile is a facility that specializes in general dental care for children, adolescents and adults. Our office is patient-friendly, our practice featuring digital x-rays (significantly less radiation than conventional film x-rays), and a warm, comfortable atmosphere. ​ Dr.Clemente is the mother of Evelyn Carolina and Veronica Michelle ages 9 and 7. She fell in love with Sanford and its community while on a road trip to different areas of Central Florida and decided this was where she wanted to raise her daughters. She is a fan of the outdoors, the ocean and a diligent Zumba dancer. Dr. Clemente loves to listen to music, run, swim and be outdoors with her daughters and her Mini Schnauzer, Fido. Dr. Clemente has a positive outlook towards life, she is passionate about her profession, loves to smile, laugh and help others in any way she can. Come meet Dr. Clemente and become part of the Amazing Smile Family!

Dr. Brad Oswald is a family oriented dentist with a strong preventative philosophy- he places an emphasis on prevention and uses materials and techniques that research has shown to be the most effective and long lasting. He feels that the best dental treatment is done in a friendly environment with kindness, courtesy and patience. Dr. Oswald continues to further his education by attending continuing education courses, seminars, and workshops every few months. Brad and his wife Kris are originally from the area. After graduating from Creighton University, they quickly moved back and now have 5 kids who are active in the community. Dr. Oswald has been serving the dental needs of Southeast Idaho since 1996. He loves to be as current as possible with the latest research, equipment, and techniques in order to provide the best quality of care possible for his patients.
education: Creighton University

full_bio: Dr. Olabi was born in Cameroon, Africa, raised in the country of Lebanon, then moved to the United States at the age of 13. He graduated from Iowa’s Dowling High School then received a Bachelors Degree in business and soccer scholarship from Grand View College in Des Moines. After graduation he relocated to Cleveland, Ohio to play professional soccer for the next 8 years in the National Professional Soccer League and the Continental Indoor Soccer League. Dr. Olabi was inducted into the Soccer Hall of Fame at Grandview University. Also, he worked as a soccer coach for children ages 5-14. After retiring from soccer, Dr. Olabi moved to Indianapolis and obtained his Doctor of Dental Surgery Degree from the Indiana University School of Dentistry and completed a General Practice Residency at Wishard Memorial Hospital. His passion for helping children inspired him to continue his studies at Riley Hospital for Children where he received his Certificate in Pediatric Dentistry and his Masters Degree in Pediatric Dentistry. Dr. Olabi is also a graduate of Progressive Orthodontic Seminars and is currently enrolled in pediatric orthodontic courses through Gerber Orthodontics. Currently, Dr. Olabi serves as an adjunct faculty and assistant clinical professor in the Pediatric Dentistry Department at the Indiana University School of Dentistry. He is an active member of the American Academy of Pediatric Dentistry, the American Dental Association, the Indiana Dental Association and the Chicago Dental Society. Dr. Olabi speaks multiple languages including Spanish, French, and Arabic.
education: Bachelors Degree from Grand View College; Doctor of Dental Surgery Degree from Indiana University School of Dentistry; Certificate in Pediatric Dentistry; Masters Degree in Pediatric Dentistry; Graduate of Progressive Orthodontic Seminars; currently enrolled in pediatric orthodontic courses through Gerber Orthodontics.
experience: Professional soccer player for 8 years; adjunct faculty and assistant clinical professor in Pediatric Dentistry Department.

full_bio: Dr. Hunter attended UC Berkeley, where she received a BA in Genetics. She received her DDS degree from Case Western Reserve University in Cleveland, Ohio. Upon her return to the Bay Area, she taught DAU on the clinic floor at UCSF Dental School, before settling into her private practice in Livermore, and motherhood. At first, she practiced dentistry in Livermore on a part time basis, in order to raise her sons. During their childhood, she was active volunteering for the local pre-schools and elementary schools, Little League, and Cub Scouts. Professionally, she has also volunteered for Expanding Your Horizons, and LCDC. She has always pursued continuing education classes avidly. From 1994 to 1996 she attended the UCSF Miniresidency in Orofacial Pain. In 1996, having passed the board exams of the American Board of Orofacial Pain, she became a Diplomate of the American Board of Orofacial Pain. She then went on to serve on the exam committee for that organization, helping to write questions for future board exams. She continues to attend both high level general dentistry classes and orofacial pain meetings throughout the country. Now that her sons are grown, she has turned her full attention to providing high quality dental care and the treatment of orofacial pain to the Livermore community. In her new, state-of-the-art facility she is able to practice full time, including Saturday hours. Professional Memberships: American Academy of Orofacial Pain (fellow) American Dental Association California Dental Association Southern Alameda County Dental Association Civic Memberships: Livermore Chamber of Commerce Livermore Downtown Association Certification: Diplomate, American Board of Orofacial Pain
education: BA in Genetics from UC Berkeley; DDS from Case Western Reserve University
experience: Practiced dentistry part time in Livermore; Taught DAU on clinic floor at UCSF Dental School; Volunteered for various organizations; Attended UCSF Miniresidency in Orofacial Pain; Diplomate of the American Board of Orofacial Pain; Continues to attend high level dentistry classes.

full_bio: As an orthodontist, I am most passionate about working with people of all ages, from all walks of life. I enjoy meeting new people and hearing about their lives and experiences. Everyone has stories to tell, and I appreciate what my patients share with me. Our conversations enrich my life. I am thankful for the joy patients bring to me and hope I give them the same. I have practiced orthodontics for over 30 years. My father was a general dentist and I went to work in his office when I was in 6 th grade. I enjoyed it so much that I decided I wanted to become a dentist. Then I had my braces put on and thought, “This is even better!” I went through a lot of changes during my orthodontic experience. I grew as a person, my personality developed, and my self-esteem blossomed. I knew that my appearance changed, and that strengthened my confidence. By the time my braces were removed, I had a smile I really loved, and couldn’t wait to share it with the world! Now I help people as they go through the same transformation. Being part of that and seeing people’s happiness with their new smiles makes this the most amazing profession! Education Bachelor of Science in biology – University of California at Irvine Doctorate of Dental Medicine – University of Pittsburgh School of Dental Medicine Master of Dental Science – University of Pittsburgh School of Dental Medicine I love learning and never want to stop. I want to keep making myself better and finding the best new approaches to benefit my patients. Throughout the year I take a lot of continuing education, through study groups as well as attending meetings, lectures, and seminars. This keeps me up to date on the latest developments and ensures I am providing the best treatment and most beautiful smiles. Professional Memberships American Association of Orthodontists Academy for Orthodontic Excellence Pacific Coast Society of Orthodontists American Dental Association California Dental Association Orange County Dental Society Beyond the Practice I grew up in Huntington Beach, lived in Pennsylvania during dental school and my postgraduate orthodontic training, then moved to back to Orange County. I’ve lived in Fountain Valley for more than 30 years and have raised my son Jay here. He graduated from Hiram College in Ohio, where he played football for four years. We have a Papillon dog, Kei, who’s a bright light in our home. When not in the office, I volunteer with the Fountain Valley Community Foundation and enjoy time with loved ones. I also like to travel, golf with Jay, scuba dive, and am an avid scrapbooker.
education: Bachelor of Science in biology – University of California at Irvine Doctorate of Dental Medicine – University of Pittsburgh School of Dental Medicine Master of Dental Science – University of Pittsburgh School of Dental Medicine
experience: over 30 years

full_bio: Dr. Baranovsky has been practicing dentistry for nearly 30 years now, and there’s nothing he enjoys more than restoring his patients’ confidence and simply making them happy through the high-quality care he provides. To learn more about his background, keep reading below: Why Did You Decide to Become a Dentist? Dr. Baranovsky originally planned to become a medical doctor, but he found himself very curious about the world of dentistry. Eventually, he chose to explore a career in oral healthcare further – and he hasn’t looked back since! Today, he still loves his life and the profession he chose all those years ago. Where Did You Study Dentistry? Originally from Ukraine, Dr. Baranovsky attended Zhytomyr Medical College. He also completed his doctorate and a residency in prosthodontics at Ivano-Frankivsk Medical Institute in Ukraine before receiving his degree in dentistry at the University of Illinois at Chicago. He continues to be passionate about continuing education and has completed courses in dental implants through the ATC Implant Institute and the Hiossen Dental Implant Research & Education Center. He is currently a member of the following organizations: American Dental Association Illinois Dental Association Academy of General Dentistry Chicago Dental Society Outside of the Dental Office, What Do You Like to Do? Dr. Baranovsky and his wife Irina have a daughter and a son. When he isn’t busy at the dental office, his personal hobbies include hiking, going on long walks, skiing, and educating others.
education: Zhytomyr Medical College; Ivano-Frankivsk Medical Institute; University of Illinois at Chicago
experience: Nearly 30 years

full_bio: When Dr. Larrabee founded Advanced Orthodontics in 2005, he had a vision: create an orthodontic practice where clinical excellence and genuine care go hand in hand. Today, that vision has earned us recognition as one of Phoenix’s Top Workplaces and made us the Valley’s trusted choice for orthodontic care. After graduating in the top 5% of his class at the prestigious University of Michigan Dental School (Go Blue!), Dr. Larrabee pursued his Masters in Orthodontics at Marquette University’s renowned two-year program. This elite training exposed him to the most advanced approaches in orthodontics, setting the foundation for his commitment to innovative care. Dr. Larrabee’s dedication to excellence shows in every smile he creates. As a Blue Diamond+ Top 1% Invisalign Provider (top 1% nationwide) and a 10-time recipient of Phoenix Magazine’s Top Doc award, he brings advanced expertise in Roth Williams techniques and specialized training in occlusion and TMJ treatment to every patient. Beyond creating beautiful smiles, Dr. Larrabee is passionate about giving back. You’ll find him supporting Phoenix Children’s Hospital, the Crohn’s and Colitis Foundation of America, and cheering on his patients at their extracurricular activities. When he’s not transforming smiles, he enjoys spending time with his wife Carly and their three children – Luke, Will, and Farrah – often coaching their sports teams and enjoying the Arizona sunshine they traded Chicago’s winters for.
education: Top 5% Graduate, University of Michigan Dental School, 2001 Masters in Orthodontics, Marquette University, 2003 Certified Specialist in Roth Williams, Occlusion, and TMJ Treatment Diamond+ Elite Invisalign Provider (Top 1% Nationwide)

full_bio: Dr. Archie, a passionate advocate for aesthetic dentistry, brings a unique blend of expertise and compassion to his practice. With a solid foundation in healthcare, having graduated with a degree in Pharmacy from Xavier University, Dr. Archie's journey took a transformative turn when he discovered his calling in dentistry. He earned his dental degree from Howard University School of Dentistry, where he honed his skills and nurtured his passion for creating beautiful smiles. Inspired by the dedication of his mentor, Dr. Leonard Breda, a beloved small-town dentist renowned for his commitment to enhancing the smiles of his patients, Dr. Archie embarked on a mission to carry forward this legacy of smile development. Dr. Breda's influence instilled in him a deep sense of responsibility towards his patients' aesthetic needs and aspirations. Driven by a desire to make a tangible difference in people's lives, Dr. Archie actively engages with his community beyond the confines of his practice. He actively participates in community health fairs, offering his expertise and guidance to those in need. Moreover, Dr. Archie serves as a mentor to high school and college-aged students, sharing his knowledge and inspiring the next generation of dental professionals. Dr. Archie's foray into the realm of esthetic dentistry was propelled by his genuine desire to address the evolving needs of his patients. Recognizing the profound impact that a beautiful smile can have on one's confidence and self-esteem, he delved deeper into the intricacies of aesthetic dental procedures. Equipped with a keen eye for detail and a commitment to excellence, Dr. Archie endeavors to exceed his patients' expectations with each smile transformation. With Dr. Archie, you can expect not just exceptional dental care, but a personalized journey towards achieving the smile of your dreams. Whether it's through cosmetic enhancements, restorative treatments, or comprehensive smile makeovers, Dr. Archie is dedicated to helping you unlock your true smile potential and radiate confidence from within.
education: Xavier University, Howard University School of Dentistry

full_bio: Welcome to Harris Family Dentistry - your oral health oasis. Growing up I found great satisfaction using my hands to fix and create things that would make people smile. This hobby eventually lead me to a career in dentistry. I have found continued joy and passion in using my hands to preserve and restore my clients’ smiles. I look forward to meeting you and maintaining your smile today! -Trevor Meet the Doc Welcome to Harris Family Dentistry! Dr. Trevor Harris was born and raised in Arkansas City, KS. He attended C4 elementary, ACMS, and graduated ACHS in 2011. During his time in high school, he played football, ran track, and was a lifeguard at the Paris Park Pool. Trevor attended a semester at Cowley College before transferring to Pittsburg State University to pursue his pre-dental studies. He graduated from Pittsburg State in 2015 with a Bachelor of Science in Biology, then spent a year as a dental assistant in Frontenac, KS. Dr. Harris graduated from the University of Missouri - Kansas City School of Dentistry in May 2020 amid the COVID-19 pandemic. Dr. Harris is married to Molly Harris (formerly Molly Warren) who is also an Ark City native. She received her doctorate degree from Wichita State University as a Family Nurse Practitioner and works at the Ark City Clinic. They have a two-year-old son, Cohen, and a baby girl, Ainsley Jo Harris, born in September 2021. It was an easy decision for their family to move back home as the community and close family will make a great place to raise children. In his spare time, Dr. Harris enjoys golfing, cooking, taking trips to the lake, and fishing. His favorite hole at the Ark City Country Club is number 17 (where he proposed to Molly) and one of his signature meals is buffalo chicken pizza he cooks on Chief’s game day. Dr. Harris is happy to be home and serving the community he was raised in.
education: Bachelor of Science in Biology from Pittsburg State University, graduated from the University of Missouri - Kansas City School of Dentistry in May 2020
experience: 1 year as a dental assistant, graduated in 2020

full_bio: Dr. Mark Kesler grew up living in many locations as his father was in the army until he retired and returned home to West Terre Haute. He graduated from West Vigo High School in 1987. After high school he served in the U.S. army for 5 years being stationed in Germany and Hawaii. After graduating from Indiana University School of Dentistry in 2002 he practiced in Fishers for a year followed by two years in Richmond. He also worked in an emergency office for a year and is very experienced with extractions. He has also done a mission trip to Haiti as well as volunteering at various locations to help those in need. He owned an office on the north side of Indianapolis for 15 years before joining us here. Dr. Kesler preforms most dental procedures to include cosmetic work like veneers and Invisalign as well as crowns, bridges, dentures, partials, and his favorite, extractions. He can communicate very clearly and works well with all types of patients to include high anxiety or nervous patients as well as all age rangers from children to elderly. He is a nice, competent, likable man and a good listener. Dr. Kesler lives in Fishers with his wife of over twenty years and his three children. His interests include his children’s activities (swimming, track, soccer, and cross country), football (Steelers), traveling to warm locations to relax, exercising (running and going to the gym) and playing with his dog Rosie. He also finds time to help his wife, Whitney, with her job as a realtor. Usually by placing open house signs for her! He considers sitting around and playing a board game great quality family time. He wants to make your experience here as pleasant as possible and prides himself on making patients comfortable while seeing to their oral care.
education: Indiana University School of Dentistry
experience: He practiced in Fishers for a year followed by two years in Richmond. He also worked in an emergency office for a year and is very experienced with extractions. He owned an office on the north side of Indianapolis for 15 years.

full_bio: Dr. Mark Arnett is a life-long resident of Murray-Calloway County. He grew up in on the farm and graduated from Calloway County High School. He did his undergraduate studies at Murray State University then went on to graduate with honors from The University of Louisville School of Dentistry in 1997. Dr. Arnett has practiced dentistry in Murray Kentucky ever since graduation. He resides on the farm with his wife Diana Ridley Arnett and his three wonderful children Michael, Alexandra, and Abbey Arnett. “There was never any doubt where I would practice and raise a family than Murray Kentucky.” In his spare time, Dr. Arnett enjoys working on the farm, gardening, traveling, hunting, woodworking, basically anything outdoor related. Professionally, he particularly enjoys working with patient to restore their self-confidence and appearance by replacing missing teeth. Whether it be single missing tooth or a total replacement of all teeth either with conventional cosmetic dentures, “snap in” dentures or permanent dentures that are permanently attached to implants. “There is nothing quite as rewarding as giving someone back their appearance, self-confidence and function that has needlessly suffered for years. That is why I do what I do.”
education: undergraduate studies at Murray State University, graduated with honors from The University of Louisville School of Dentistry in 1997

full_bio: Background Hometown: Davisburg, MI Dental School: University of Michigan School of Dentistry , DDS Orthodontic Residency: University of Louisville School of Dentistry, MS and Certificate in Orthodontics Q&A: Why should we choose you as an Orthodontist? I see communication as one of my strengths as an Orthodontist. I see myself as a very compassionate person and doctor, but I’m also a big fan of open communication with patients and parents, even when they can be involved, hard conversations. I want to know your concerns first; I want you to know mine second; and I want to tackle them all in a way that is best for all of us so we can give you or your child the best smile with the healthiest bite possible. So you’re an Orthodontist, what else do you like to do besides move teeth? Dr. Anthony and I are big outdoor enthusiasts-- we love hiking, camping, golfing, and even simple walks with our pup, Riggins. I also love to cook and entertain friends and family. When I’m not in Colorado, I can be found back “Up North” in Michigan, floating in a boat at our family’s lake cottage. What are some areas of your life that you’d like to “Ascend” in? I have been so blessed to become a mom in recent years and that is one area of my life that I continually strive to “Ascend” in. Like so many of our patient families know, being a mom (or dad), while challenging, is oh so sweet. Dr. Anthony and I are so grateful to be in a profession that allows us to invest time with our kids (You’ll likely see them running around the office from time to time!) fun facts: I have a passion and dare I say talent for creating charcuterie boards! I’ve always been a health and fitness nut. You can find me wandering around a Farmer’s Market or getting in a session on our spin bike! I’ve developed a self-taught dabbling in graphic design. While I am certainly no professional, I love to create new, unique pieces--including our logo!
education: Dental School: University of Michigan School of Dentistry , DDS Orthodontic Residency: University of Louisville School of Dentistry, MS and Certificate in Orthodontics

full_bio: Background Hometown: Okemos, MI University of Michigan School of Dentistry , DDS University of Connecticut School of Dental Medicine, MS and Certificate in Orthodontics Q&A: Why Orthodontics? I’ve always had slight tendencies towards an “exacting” personality, so much so that as a young kid I would drive my parents crazy with how obsessive I was on where the seam of my socks fit. If it wasn’t just right, I needed new socks! Luckily, in dental school I found a new, better avenue for my obsession - perfecting people’s smiles :) I love that orthodontics allows me the opportunity to transform a smile, and it is in the final detailing that I really find my passion (and allow my meticulousness an outlet). I truly believe Dr. Carly and I are blessed to be able to practice Orthodontics. What is one mountain you’re proud to have submitted? While I’ve not tackled a 14er yet (on my bucket list), I have become a husband and a dad in recent years and those are two pretty great “peaks”! What’s your favorite ski area? I have to pick a home state resort as one of my favorites! While we don’t get down there as often as we’d like, I think Telluride has both the best views and the most exciting runs. Plus, the town has fun activities for anyone not skiing during the day and so many restaurant options for the family afterwards! FUN FACTS: When I was in college I played Club Baseball at the University of Michigan, and during our regional tournament we got to play in the stadium that “A League of Their Own” was filmed. When I was 12, I got lost on a ski mountain for what seemed like hours. I accidentally skied too far ahead of our group (because I loved going straight and fast) and ended up separated from everyone. This happened at Heavenly resort in California; now I make sure to always keep an eye on the group here in Colorado! One of my favorite movies is the Guardians of the Galaxy, and I especially love Groot! We even have a Baby Groot figurine sitting on a windowsill of our home.
education: University of Michigan School of Dentistry , DDS University of Connecticut School of Dental Medicine, MS and Certificate in Orthodontics

full_bio: A Texarkana native, Dr. Lunsford did his undergraduate school at both TC and A&M of Texarkana before graduating from UALR with a BS in Biology and a minor in Chemistry. He received his Doctorate of Dental Surgery in July 2015, from the University of Tennessee Health Science Center in Memphis, TN. Dr. Reese enjoys hunting, fishing, and loves his dogs. Dr. Reese looks forward to serving the Little River County and surrounding areas.
